title: hot chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of a pie plate.
Layer chili and chopped green chilies.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with large Fritos.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, walnuts and cinnamon; mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: new fashioned apple cobbler
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup apple juice.
Set aside. Combine remaining juice and next five ingredients in a pan.
Let boil and reduce heat.
Simmer.
Stir in 1 cup starch mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils for 1 minute.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove and pour in a pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, melted margarine and one egg, beating until combined.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture. Spread remaining mixture in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, pressing to form an even crust.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: You will need one pint size zip type plastic bag and 1 gallon size zip type plastic bag.

title: real red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, cocoa and milk alternately. Add soda mixture, extract and food coloring.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans.	Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandma's knishes
directions: All ingredients are to be at room temperature.
Dissolve yeast in two tablespoons warm water.
Mix 2 cups of flour with remaining ingredients.
Add yeast mixture.
Up to this point, a mixer can be used.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the remaining flour.
Allow mixture to stand for an hour.
(It may be refrigerated.)
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: deep dish curried chicken pie
directions: Melt butter or oleo;
add
onion,
garlic,
celery
and apple. Cook and stir for
5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and curry. Add salt, pepper and
bay leaf.
Add chicken broth and stir until sauce thickens.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes; add chicken, cream, chutney and
cook for 1 minute.
Pour into casserole;
fill so pastry
doesn't
sag.
Cool
some
before covering with pastry; brush
rim
with egg yolk.
Leave margin with
pastry; then trim.
Cut
slits
in
pastry.
Place
dish under casserole. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: good ole lemonade
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir.
Stir in sugar to taste. Chill.
Serve in a tall glass on ice.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Pour chilled evaporated milk into a medium size bowl; whip with an electric mixer until soft peaks form, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix water, lemon juice and gelatin in microwave bowl; heat on High for 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve gelatin.
Mix whipped milk, sugar, food coloring and gelatin mixture with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie crust; cover and chill until fully set (1 hour).

title: strawberry truffle
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Beat well.
In a medium bowl, mix glaze and condensed milk.
In a large brandy snifter or glass container, assemble,
beginning
with	cake, then the glaze mixture, then pudding.
Continue	to
layer.
When
all
are
used, top with whipped
topping and garnish with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: best pound cake ever
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Start in cold oven, then bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Freezes well.
Serve with strawberries, ice cream, anything you like!

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low setting for 7 hours or more.

title: broken pretzel snack
directions: Break pretzels into bite-sized pieces.
Melt butter.
Add Soup mix and chili powder.
In very large bowl, pour mixture over pretzels.
Stir until coated.
Put in large roasting pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250 degrees.
Stirring 2 - 3 times.
Cool 1 or 2 hours. Put in covered container.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan to 350°.
Add noodles and cook until puffed and crisp, about 5 seconds.
Do not let brown. Using slotted spoon, transfer noodles to paper towels.
Whisk rice vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, wasabi and red pepper in medium bowl. Gradually whisk in both oils.
Heat 1/4 cup dressing in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and saute until cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Transfer chicken to small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
(Can be prepared 4 hours ahead.
Let noodles stand at room temperature.
Keep chicken refrigerated.)
Combine noodles, chicken, lettuce, bell peppers and herbs in large bowl.
Toss with enough remaining dressing to season to taste.
Divide salad among plates and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hope's mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, pecans and butter. Mix well. Pat this mixture into bottom of 10 x 13 pan. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes. Take out and cool thoroughly. Mix cream cheese, 8 ounces Cool Whip and sugar. Spread over cooled crust. Mix chocolate pudding and sweet milk. Pour this over cream cheese layer. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(Any other fresh fruit or canned can also be used.)

title: pot pie squares
directions: Combine
sifted flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in Crisco as for pastry.
Add water to beaten egg and combine with flour mixture.
Roll out very thin on floured board; cut into squares.
Add
to simmering pot pie ingredients, cooking until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine with hamburger, cook for 1/2 hour more.
You can double recipe, as it freezes well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix salt, pepper, vinegar, oil, water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Cool and pour over combined vegetables.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tarra's favorite chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken and tear meat off bone.
Mix celery, onion and celery seed in broth after removing chicken.
Bring to boil.
Add fettucine noodles.
Let cook for 1 hour.
Serve while hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soups, broth, rice, bell pepper, shallots and parsley together.
Mix well.
Season pork chops.
Place mixture in large casserole dish.
Put pork chops on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Remove, cover and bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: marinated vegetables(8 servings)
directions: Drain peas and beans. Rinse with cold water and drain again. Combine with all remaining ingredients.
Stir gently to mix well. Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve as a side dish or salad. Since this combination contains no eggs or mayonnaise, it is a good choice for picnics or cookouts.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken fillets into small strips.
Place in dish. Sprinkle with ginger.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Remove ginger.
Add seasoned salt, brown sugar and pepper; mix well. Heat sesame oil and vegetable oil in wok.
Add chicken mixture; stir-fry until 3/4 cooked.
Add onion and soy sauce.
Stir-fry until chicken is tender.
Drizzle with lemon juice; mix gently. Remove from heat.
Serves 4.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Can freeze half to use later.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: regan dodd's viennese fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, the sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon of water. Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in pecans.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Place a layer of uncooked lasagna noodles on bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pound raw ground beef.
Add 1/2 jar of spaghetti sauce, then 1/2 of cottage cheese. Repeat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Add Mozzarella cheese last 20 minutes of baking.

title: baked apples with equal sugar
directions: Core each apple.
In center, put butter, raisins and sugar. Pour just about 1/2 water in pan.
Baste apples as they cook.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Add about 2 tablespoons flour for high altitudes.

title: hash 'n cheese grill
directions: Mix hash, catsup, onion, parsley flakes and oregano; spread on muffin halves.
Top with cheese strips.
Broil 8 to 10-inches from heat until cheese is melted and hash mixture is bubbly and hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook.
Stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in 1 cup of the cheese until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese sauce.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with 1 cup Cool Whip and sugar. Beat well and spread over the crust.
For next layer, mix pudding with milk.
Beat until thickened and spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over this and sprinkle with coconut.
(Chocolate pudding mix works well, also.)

title: special chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, pineapple, oranges, celery, olives and green onions in a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise and mustard together and gently stir into chicken mixture.
Cover the salad and refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Slice zucchini into 1/2-inch slices. Parboil until it changes color; let cool slightly.
Blend together soup and melted butter.
Layer zucchini, tomatoes (sliced), thinly sliced onions, sauce and half of the cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: dump cherry cake
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Empty pie filling.
Add pineapple with juice.
Spread cake mixture on top; press down evenly.
Melt margarine; drip over cake mix.
Spread pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tangy cabbage salad
directions: Combine prepared vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill well.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Blend shortening, sugar and eggs; add flour mixture and then add oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop from a spoon on a cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven until edges begin to brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix on top, spreading evenly.
Add pecans.
Pour margarine on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes in 3 (8-inch or 9-inch) pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Separate eggs, beat yolks and honey until light and creamy. Add carrots, nuts, flour and cinnamon.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When cool, top with mixture of softened cream cheese mixed with lemon and orange.

title: green beans with walnuts and walnut oil
directions: Cook beans in a large pot of boiling water until just tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse; melt butter in skillet.
Add oil and beans.
Toss until heated through.
Add walnuts and parsley.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Drain raspberries; drain pineapple (reserve juice).
Add orange juice to reserved pineapple juice.
Dissolve jello in the boiling water.
Add juice and chill until partially set.
Add raspberries and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: poppy seed ham sandwiches
directions: Melt butter.
Grate onion.
Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, poppy seed, mustard and onion together.
Slice buns in half and lay top part of buns aside.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Brown ground beef (drain).
Combine Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of chicken soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, put one layer of Doritos and 4 slices of cheese, then put enough of the Ro-Tel mixture to cover chips and cheese.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: taco casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer corn chips or taco shells, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and chili.

title: savory clam balls
directions: Pour both cans of clams, plus the liquid from one of the cans, into a large mixing bowl.
Crush crackers with rolling pin or blender, but not too fine.
Add crumbs and seasonings to clams. Add melted butter and mix very thoroughly.
Mixture should be thick enough to hold its shape when formed into little balls.
If it is too liquidy, open second box of crackers, crush and add a few at a time.
Shape mixture into 3/4-inch balls.
Put balls on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 or 15 minutes. Place on a hot tray and serve with fancy toothpicks.
Makes about 70, depending on how small you make them.
Make the day before and refrigerate overnight in covered container.
This allows seasonings to blend.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water well before putting on stove. When it starts to boil, cover for 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook to 265°.
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites in electric mixer bowl; add salt and vanilla.
When hot syrup reaches 265°, pour from height of 1 foot into beaten egg whites (keep beating until stiff enough to hold shape when dropped from spoon and loses it gloss).
Add walnuts while syrup and egg whites are being beaten together.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes; add refried beans.
Crush Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture on top, then cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with chopped lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, and salt until browned.
Drain. Mix with rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pineapple squares
directions: Combine margarine and the 1/4 cup sugar with fork.
Blend in flour until crumbs form, then mix thoroughly with hands until soft dough is formed.
Press into 9-inch square or 7 x 11 pan.
Prick dough with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and spread with pineapple evenly (use juice for drinking). Combine beaten egg with sugar and melted margarine; stir in pineapple.
Spread mixture evenly over pineapple.
Return to oven and bake 17 to 20 minutes, until topping is nicely browning.
Cool in pan, then cut.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat eggs and sugar together.
Add oil, juice and vanilla; beat well.
Put apples in medium bowl with sugar and cinnamon; toss and set aside.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Pour half the batter; top with half the apples.
Pour rest of batter on top; add the rest of apples. Bake 1 hour or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: cheese roll
directions: Double recipe.
Set out until soft.
Roll in chili powder. Store in refrigerator.

title: buffalo chips or mock heath bars
directions: Put whole crackers on jelly roll pan; spread pecans all over. Mix butter, margarine and sugar in small pan, bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, break Hershey bars into small pieces. Put on top of crackers as soon as they come out of oven.
When chocolate melts some, swirl all over crackers.
Put all in refrigerator for about 15 minutes.
Break into pieces.
Keep in tin.
Can be frozen.

title: blanket franks
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish, place 6 slices of bread. Cover with hot dogs and cheese. Top with the rest of the bread.
Pour on combined mixture of eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Refrigerate 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake franks for 1 hour before serving.

title: bourbon frankfurter appetizers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Mix well.
Stir in frankfurters.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: quick baked cheese dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 1\2 hour.
Serve with assorted cut up vegtables.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: grandma rose banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray loaf pans with Pam and add mixture 3/4 full.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until the toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Good luck!

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix meat loaf and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until no pink remains.
Drain; spoon pizza sauce over meat loaf and sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped artichoke hearts
directions: Cut bacon into halves.
Wrap artichoke with bacon and secure with toothpick. Broil until bacon is browned, about 5 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage and onion.
Heat Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve with chips.

title: austrian rolls
directions: Scald milk and dissolve shortening in it.
Strain mashed potatoes through sieve into milk; let cool.
Beat egg in large bowl; add sugar, salt and milk mixture.
Then add dry yeast, which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup flour at a time, mixing well.
Rub top of bread and sides of bowl with shortening and let rise in warm place until double in size (about an hour).
Punch down and shape half of dough into 36 small balls. Put 3 balls into each cup of 12-cup muffin tin.
Let rise again for about an hour, then bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until blended and smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit, pretzel sticks, etc.
Makes 2 cups.
Contains approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: chocolate oatmeal fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, cocoa and sugar.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites; slowly add sugar, then vanilla.
Add crackers and nuts.
Bake in a buttered pie tin 1/2 hour at 300°.
Cool; top with sweetened strawberries and whipped topping.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas coated nuts
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Whisk egg white until frothy.
Mix in nuts until well coated.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove; cool on foil.

title: thin mints
directions: Put 2/3 of almond bark and chocolate chips in bowl.
Microwave 2 1/2 to 3 minutes to melt.
Put half of this on wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.
Let the rest set at room temperature.
Microwave other 1/3 of almond bark for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until soft.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Add cream until smooth enough to spread on chocolate layer.
Cool and top with the rest of chocolate.
Cool.
To cut, bring to room temperature.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake in 350°
oven.
Watch closely to not overbake. Decorate as desired.

title: easy pizza snacks
directions: Cover bagels with pizza sauce and cheese.
Add choice toppings (sausage).
Cook in oven until cheese is melted and bagel is warm.

title: chicken de mayonnaise
directions: If you can't get capers and chow chow pickles, use 2 tablespoons Durkee dressing and 1/2 cup chopped sour pickles. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Mix the rest in well.
Put in a well-greased bowl and cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep for a week.
When ready to use, take out what you want to let rise about 1 hour.
Makes about 4 dozen rolls.

title: kathy's chili
directions: In a large pan, fry the hamburger, sausage and onion.
Drain fat.
In a large pot, add the beans and tomatoes.
Add the meat and stir.
Add tomato juice to desired thickness.
Add the chili mix seasoning and garlic salt.
Simmer and serve.
Garnish with Fritos and American cheese.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread onto tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Roll tightly.
Wrap each in wax paper and chill 2 hours.
Slice into 1-inch rolls and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Pour salt over sliced cucumbers and stir.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse slightly.
mix cucumbers and spices in enamel kettle, bring to a boil.
Pack in sterilized jars while hot.
Seal immediately.

title: souper pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place in casserole.
Top with soup and water.
Let bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: tuna chef salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill. Toss remaining ingredients together.
Pour chilled dressing over and toss lightly.
Serves 8. Contains 78 calories.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in blender and mix.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended. Heat in microwave until cheese is melted. Add hot pepper sauce if desired and mix well. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Place mushroom caps right side up on foil-lined broiler pan. Brush tops of caps with 1 tablespoon oil. Broil 5 to 10 minutes until tender; drain and set aside. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet over high heat. Cook and stir mushroom stems, red pepper and onion 5 minutes or until almost dry. Add mustard and seasonings.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon vegetable mixture into each mushroom cap. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil 5 minutes until browned. Garnish with parsley.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute salt pork and onions over low heat until onions are tender.
Add carrots, celery, pepper, can of tomatoes plus 1 can of water.
Add potato chunks when vegetables are 1/2 done.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, 1 cup sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons water in saucepan on low heat until boiling.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons cold water, add to rhubarb.
Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Beat egg yolks with fork slightly.
Stir some of the hot mixture in, then add to rhubarb.
Then cool.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Place chicken, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, oregano, garlic and black pepper in a large bowl.
Mix so chicken is well coated. Refrigerate, covered for 24 hours.
(You can also put some of the marinade and chicken into ziplock bags and freeze until needed.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt oleo; stir in sugar. Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add chocolate chips and coconut. Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy crust for fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and sugar.
Add enough water to spread easily.
Place fruit in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish with 1/4 cup of margarine and sugar to taste.
Place in microwave; cook until margarine is melted.
Place loaf bread on fruit.
Pour mixture of flour, sugar, margarine and water on loaf bread.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: army bread
directions: On the bark of maples and, sometimes, beeches and birches in northern woods, a green broad leaved lichen grows, known as lungwort, liverwort, lung lichen, and lungmoss which works as yeast.
Gather and steep overnight in lukewarm water.
In the morning, add enough flour to make a good batter.
Place sponge in warm place and cover with cloth.
By evening, it will have risen. Leaven dough (save some), rise overnight and bake next morning. Never freeze!

title: snappers
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Beat in the chocolate chips.
Combine and mix in the flour and baking powder.
Stir in the peanut butter chips and chopped nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pint jar.
Shake well to blend. Spoon over fresh fruit or fruit salad.

title: gods own barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk tomato puree and mustard; add remaining ingredients. Slowly heat to boil; reduce heat to simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm as dipping sauce.
Will keep refrigerated for several weeks.

title: cream cheese rounds
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl; beat at high speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder; beat into cream cheese mixture.
Shape dough into a ball; wrap in plastic wrap and chill until firm. Roll dough on a floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/4-inch round cutter and place on greased cookie sheets.
Make an indention in center of each round with back of a spoon.
Place 1 teaspoon preserves in center of each round.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May store for up to 1 week in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hot green cider
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except extract. Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Add extract.
Serve hot or chill and serve over ice cubes with Sweet*10.
Makes 14 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: quick fudge, quick gone
directions: Boil sugar and water 1 to 2 minutes, full boil.
Remove from stove, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well, pour into greased pan.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix, but do not heat.
Put in 1 gallon jar.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers thin (about 8) and 2 medium onions.
Fill to top of jar and place in refrigerator.
Ready in 3 or 4 days and will keep indefinitely.

title: angel food deluxe cake
directions: Sift together flour and confectioners sugar.
Set aside.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of deep casserole.
Cover rice with chicken, one layer.
Stir soup, water and onion soup together. Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover last 20 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: oatmeal candy cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper lined pan.
Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: party dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco sauce.
Spread on serving platter.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion, black olives and cheese.
Serve with Fritos.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions on package.
Have grits stiff, not soupy.
Melt in oleo and garlic cheese. Beat eggs and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add egg and milk mixture to grits and cheese mixture.
Put in well-buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle crumbled, cooked bacon, grated cheese and paprika on top.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: creamy lo-cal dressing
directions: Mix ingredients with blender until smooth.

title: green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; in saucepan, put green beans, onion and brown sugar and cook 1 hour on medium heat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until creamy.
Add food coloring and cool.
Combine with strawberries and pour into cooked crust with a little sugar in the bottom.
Add whipped cream on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer or hen until done; debone.
In broth, add cream of mushroom soup and bring to a boil.
Add rolled and cut biscuits or cut tortillas, a few at a time.
Lower your fire.
When done, add chopped eggs, deboned chicken and salt and pepper to taste.

title: just like luby's shredded carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with onion and pepper; drain.
Cook noodles and celery together for 10 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: In a bowl, stir together the 1 cup cornmeal, baking soda and salt.
Stir in milk, eggs and corn.
Stir in cheese, chili peppers (chopped) and onion; mix until well blended.

title: lincoln's favorite cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Add almonds and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, to which salt has been added.
Bake at 350° in 3 layers in 8 or 9-inch pans for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown chuck in skillet until done; drain and set aside.
Over low heat, melt the 2 cheeses.
Add the soups (no water) and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir well.
Add the ground chuck to cheese mixture and blend well.
Best to keep dip warm in crock-pot.
Can be refrigerated to be used at a later date.
Serve with hot peppers and chips.

title: scripture cake
directions: This cake is sort of a fruit and nut cake.
So get out the family Bible and follow directions.
Only part from our recipe is how long to bake, but a moderate oven (360° to 375°) has worked. Check figures, too.

title: skinny chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl, mixing well.
Chill to serving temperature.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.

title: rice consomme
directions: Saute onions and rice until brown in margarine.
Put in casserole and add oregano and mushrooms.
Add soup.
Add parsley flakes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Note:
If nuts are omitted, use 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips.

title: yummy yams
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and slice.
Fill skillet with 1/2-inch of water.
Place sweet potatoes, sugar and butter in water.
Cover skillet.
Cook on medium-high heat until potatoes are tender.

title: best-ever muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill muffin cups, greased, 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: canned pumpkin bread
directions: You will also need 8 or 9 wide mouth pint canning jars with lids and rings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Put in well greased miniature muffin pan. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Can also be dropped by spoon fulls onto cookie sheet.

title: strawberry salad delight
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch glass container, mix jello, water, bananas, pineapple and strawberries and jell completely.

title: carrot-parsnip-ginger soup
directions: Chop onion; peel and slice carrots and parsnips into 1/2-inch slices.
Grate 1 cup ginger (remainder can be stored in freezer for future use).
Heat oil; add chopped onion and cook over low heat with lid on until wilted.
Add carrots, parsnips and grated ginger; mix well, then raise heat to medium.
Replace lid and cook for a further 5 to 10 minutes.
Add hot chicken stock; bring to boil, then simmer slowly until vegetables are tender.
Liquidize in blender until smooth; strain into bowl.
Adjust seasoning with salt, pepper and more grated ginger, if required.
May be frozen. Yield:
8 servings.

title: kale soup
directions: Cover kale, onions and meat with water.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add can of beans. Cook last 5 minutes.
Enjoy with Portuguese bread.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage, onion and garlic; drain grease. Cut sauerkraut with scissors into fine pieces. Place cream cheese, 2 tablespoons bread crumbs, mustard, pepper and sauerkraut in bowl; mix well (may need to use your hands). Add sausage; chill for 1/2 hour.

title: roasted pesto potatoes
directions: Heat over to 425°.
Coat jellyroll pan with cooking spray. In bowl, toss potatoes with 1 tbsp. olive oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Transfer to pan.
Roast, turning once until tender, about 40 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine basil, parsley, parmesan and garlic with remaining olive oil.
Toss roasted potatoes with basil mixture.
Transfer to serving bowl.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in next 5 ingredients. Cover and chill for several hours. Form mixture into a ball. Roll ball in peanuts to coat well. Serve with crackers.

title: english tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough.

title: coconut joy bars
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add to sugar and coconut and mix well. Press flat into 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan.
Slowly melt chocolate chips, stirring constantly.
Spread evenly over coconut mixture and allow to cool.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients well with a fork.
Make 3 holes in mixture.
Divide vanilla, vinegar and oil into the 3 holes.
Pour over this, 2 cups cold water.
Mix everything together well with fork.
Put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
May sift powdered sugar on top or frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Heat 1 cup boiling water and add Jell-O.
Add pineapple, buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Cool and let set before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients
and
pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15
minutes;
reduce oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Break about 1 cup of pretzels.
Pour melted butter over pretzels and bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage; drain well.
Combine with other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blue cheese dressing or dip
directions: Prepare 24 hours in advance.
Better that way.
Makes a great veggie dip.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan arrange chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: vege-steak o'brien
directions: Bread Choplets and fry in oil; set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1 cup French fried onions.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange Choplets on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes until onions are brown.

title: chicken casserole(simple)
directions: Cook chicken and cut in bite size pieces.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Add broth and soup.
Melt margarine; add milk and black pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Prepare pudding with milk per directions.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in cake mix and mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 28 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables as directed along with 1 cup celery.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix onion, cheese and mayo and spread over vegetables.
Melt oleo and add to crushed crackers.
Spread over vegetable mixture.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 30 minutes. Delicious!!

title: ground round and beans
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then add beans and barbecue sauce.
Serve hot.

title: egg noodles with german meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread, half of onions, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In Dutch oven or large pot, combine remaining onions, sugar, raisins, sauerkraut, gingersnaps and tomato sauce. Add meatballs and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked and drained noodles.
Serves 4.

title: turtle
directions: Make cake as called for.
Use sheet pan. Pour half cake in pan.
Cook for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out and cool. While cooling, put in saucepan butter, milk and caramels.
Cook until melted to a thick syrup.
Pour over cooked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts, then add uncooked cake mix.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool!
Serve very small pieces.
This is very rich.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil.
Toss other ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in double boiler. Mix thoroughly. Cook over double boiler while beating constantly with electric mixer until it forms peaks (about 7 minutes). Remove from heat. Add vanilla while still beating.

title: tex-mex(low-fat)
directions: Using a pizza pan, layer ingredients in the following order: beans, sour cream mixed with taco seasoning, tomatoes, onions, olives and shredded cheese.
Serve chilled with no-fat nachos.

title: chicken fettuccine primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, heat bouillon and milk until hot.
In skillet, heat margarine.
Add vegetables, garlic and parsley; cook until tender.
Stir flour into vegetables.
Add broth mixture to vegetables slowly, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add chicken and Parmesan; toss with hot fettuccine.

title: no bake corn flake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and cook to a good boil. Remove from the heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper.

title: honey moist cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir together flour, meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients until moistened. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl shredded lettuce and 3 or 4 boiled eggs (sliced).
Layer onions, carrots, cheese, green pepper and sliced cucumbers.
Add 1 small can green peas and diced tomatoes. Crumble bacon to top.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix until well blended.
Pour into baked pie shell or prepared pie shell.
Chill.

title: pavlova dessert
directions: Lightly dampen grease-proof paper or aluminum foil cut in a 9-inch circumference. Beat egg whites until stiff and frothy. Gradually add sugar and beat until thick. Fold in sifted cornstarch and lemon juice. Spread into volcano shape on grease-proof paper. Bake in slow oven, 250°, for
2 hours. Turn oven off and leave in oven until cool. Decorate with whipped cream, strawberries, kiwi fruit, bananas.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and half of milk.
Add beaten eggs and mix. Add rest of milk.
Fold in melted butter.
Add vanilla and stir. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake until done, until knife inserted in middle comes clean.

title: yuletide punch
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of brandy and set aside.
Pour remaining brandy, champagne, sugar and pineapple into a large saucepan. Stir frequently over medium heat until near boiling.
Remove from heat.
Carefully pour in reserved brandy and ignite.
Let punch flame 1 minute, then ladle into mugs.

title: baked rice and pineapple
directions: Arrange a layer of boiled rice in bottom of buttered casserole dish and cover with canned pineapple, cut into small wedges.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
End with a layer of rice.
Moisten with pineapple juice and bake 1 hour (covered) at 350°.

title: upside-down casserole
directions: Day Before:
Cook macaroni until tender, drain.
In hot butter in a large skillet saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Spread over the bottom of a 2-quart casserole (greased) dish.
Toss macaroni with grated cheese, arrange on top of meat and tomato mixture in the casserole dish, packing it down.
Combine eggs and milk, pour over macaroni.
Cover and refrigerate until the next day.

title: yvonne's crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on miniature sliced party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix all wet ingredients in another bowl. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients, mixing well (do not beat).
Spoon mixture into three 9-inch round well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool completely. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans over cake. Refrigerate.
Flavor intensifies upon standing 24 hours.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add molasses and egg. Mix flour with soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger. Use small size cookie baller and dip in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Lightly spray cookie sheets. Press down very slightly. Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: inez arledge's german salad
directions: Layer 1/2
of the ingredients in order given in a large salad bowl.
Repeat
layers
with
other
ingredients. Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Top with pieces of bacon and enjoy!

title: seasoned crackers and pretzels
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pour over crackers or pretzels. Mix and let set at least one hour before serving.
Can be made ahead.

title: buttersnap cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake and eggs.
Mix until dough begins to form a ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Remove 1/4 dough; keep remainder chilled.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes or rounds with floured cookie cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes, until golden on edges.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Make well in center.
Stir together buttermilk, applesauce, egg whites and oil in a small bowl.
Pour this mixture into well of dry ingredients.
Stir just until evenly moistened; do not overmix.
Divide batter evenly into 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool muffins on wire rack.

title: grammpa's scottish soup
directions: Chop onions and boil until tender in small amount of water. Mash tomatoes with juice and add to onions and water; mix.
Bring to low simmer and add American cheese until it breaks into small particles throughout.
Leftovers will thicken in refrigerator and are fabulous eaten warmed over buttered toast.

title: stir-fry meal-in-one(low-fat)
directions: In large skillet or wok, cook bacon and onion until transparent.
Add chicken; continue cooking about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size chunks.
Flour, add salt and pepper to taste and enough water to make gravy.
Cook over a large fire (465°) for 4 weeks.
Serves around 3,812 people.
If more is needed, add the 2 rabbits, however, only if necessary because most people do not like hares in their stew.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour, eggs, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(Makes 2 pies.)

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use well greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: extraordinary fudge
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together.
Blend for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with crack; if it looks doughy in crack, bake longer.
Will not hurt if top looks brown because frosting makes it soft.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat. Add meat and brown. Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and re-heat through. Serve over noodles, dry Chinese noodles or rice.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Combine and mix for 3 minutes in electric mixer. Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken on the grill
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and remove from the heat.
As chicken approaches a well cooked state, baste them with sauce. When chickens are completely cooked, dip chickens into the sauce before serving.
This recipe makes over a gallon of sauce.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Put the first 10 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with the Italian dressing, sesame oil and garlic salt and pepper to taste. Shake well.
Marinate for 1 hour or overnight for a quick, delicious lo-cal salad.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cover pan; bring to rolling boil.
Remove cover and cook to 242° or until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
Just before syrup is ready, beat until stiff enough to hold a point 2 egg whites.
Pour hot syrup very slowly in a thin stream into the beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat until frosting holds peak.
Blend in vanilla.
When spreading on cake, make pretty swirls with vanilla.
Amount:
For 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers or 13 x 9-inch oblong.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in dark brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil hard 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk. Return pan to heat and bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
If frosting is too thick, add a little milk.

title: kennett square mushroom rolls
directions: Saute the mushrooms and onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add the cream cheese and seasoning.
Remove crusts from bread; flatten with rolling pin.
Spread mushroom mixture on bread slices.
Roll up slices; dip into melted butter.
Partially freeze before cutting each roll into 3 pieces.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; lower with brine solution made by mixing water and salt.
Let stand 24 hours.
Bring to boil in same solution. Drain.

title: carrot dressing
directions: Whirl in blender for 2 minutes.
Serve over equal parts shredded red and green cabbage.
Top with chopped scallions. Makes 2 cups.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice in top of a double boiler. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Cool.
Add salt and fruit to marshmallow mix.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into an 8-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: blueberry cream pie(like mom used to make; makes 2 pies)
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar well.
Make Dream Whip as if you were using it for whipped cream.
Fold Dream Whip into the cream cheese mixture.
Line bottom of pie crust with sliced bananas (after rolling bananas in lemon juice).
Pour cheese mixture over bananas and spoon pie filling on top.
Place in refrigerator.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder; blend well.
Wrap small amount of dough around one mini Snickers candy. Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Let cool and drizzle melted chocolate chips over top.
(May need to add small amount of water to thin.)

title: sausage stroganoff
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add mushrooms, garlic, tomato paste, water, beef bouillon, salt and pepper; mix together well.
Add 1/2 cup red wine; mix well.
Combine sour cream and 1 tablespoon flour; add to mixture.
Let simmer.
Cook egg noodles until done.
Rinse and stir into stroganoff mixture.

title: spinach pie(quiche)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add flour, seasonings and milk.
Stir and cook until smooth and thick, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat eggs.
Add sauce, spinach, and cheese mix.
Spray 9 inch pan with pam and pour in mixture.
Bake until top is puffed and browned, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Add when it is hard boiling, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon vinegar. Cook until crunchy. Pour over. Make into balls (butter hands).

title: cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, then add sausage and mix.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat together butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in chocolate chips. Spread in 10 x 13-inch baking pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Better and moister than Toll House pan cookies.

title: vietnamese saigon sate
directions: Mix sugar, salt, sesame seed, onion powder and garlic powder together.
Add pork and toss gently to coat.
Set aside to marinate for 30 minutes.
Put meat on wooden skewers and grill or broil over high heat for 3 to 4 minutes a side or until desired doneness. Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except apples.
Put on top of apples in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Then slowly add to wet mixture. Continue to knead in flour mixture until dough can be rolled out on a floured board.
Cut in circles.
Bake 350 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: taffy pull
directions: Mix sugar, water, butter and cream of tartar in saucepan and place over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat (do not stir) until a firm ball can be made by dropping a bit into cold water, or 250° by candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add to softened butter and coconut. Add buttermilk.
Stir well, then add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spicy fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg.
Coat with remaining ingredients mixed together.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook sausage and drain off all fat.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit lush
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with 2 sticks butter; add walnuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat up sides a bit.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until you can smell it.
Mix together and spread on cooled crust.
Cream the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Soak
beans
overnight.
On
platter, pour salsa; place cornbread on top of salsa and black beans on top of cornbread. Top with sour cream.

title: cheese chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Stir in shredded chicken, 1 cup cheese, sour cream and hot sauce.
Roll each crescent roll to a 1/4 inch to 1/8 inch thickness.
Spread with 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture.
Roll up, make sure edges are sealed.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sweet potatoes, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, 1/4 cup butter, eggs, vanilla and granulated sugar until smooth.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup butter, brown sugar, flour and pecans together (crumbles). Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add catsup, water, lemon juice, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and mustard.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frankfurters; simmer an additional 5 minutes, or until franks are thoroughly heated. To serve, place in buns and spoon sauce on top.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bridal salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed using pineapple juice with water.
Let set until it just starts to set, then beat in cream cheese and Miracle Whip, then stir in the rest of ingredients and enjoy.

title: mexican shuffle
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add refried beans, salt and 1 teaspoon chili powder and mix.
In separate saucepan, combine the mushroom soup, tomato soup, olives and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Mix and heat.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, in soup mixture to soften.
Put tortillas on a plate and put a heaping tablespoonful of the meat-bean mixture on the tortilla and roll up.
Slide rolled tortillas gently into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and repeat the procedure, until all the tortillas and meat are used.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top of tortillas. Sprinkle with shredded cheese; cover pan loosely with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes to a coarse mush, using fork and knife.
Add cheese and mayo; mix.
Bake in an oven-proof dish at 350° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Serve warm.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Turn into well-greased bread pan; bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mary liz daniel's cranberry salad
directions: Put washed, raw berries and whole orange with skin included (remove seeds) through a meat grinder twice.
Mix well with sugar and let stand.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in water and cool until partially set.
Add cranberries and other ingredients; cool until firm.
Using ring mold, fill center with cottage cheese at serving time.

title: nut brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick beef stew with dumplings
directions: Brown beef cubes in 4-quart saucepan.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add soup and vegetables. Bring to a full boil and add dumplings.

title: cherry fluff frosting
directions: Put egg white, sugar, maraschino cherry and corn syrup in top of double boiler and mix thoroughly.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly with beater until mixture will hold a peak (about 7 minutes).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil zucchini and onion together, then drain.
Combine butter, eggs, cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Mix in zucchini and onion.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle crumb mixture over zucchini casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream together. Add vanilla, potato chips and flour; mix well.
Drop cookies from a teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot and place on paper towels to cool.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water. Add boiling water and sugar. Stir. Add pineapple and lemon juice. Let congeal slightly. Mix 2 packages Dream Whip as directed. Add to congealed mixture. Break cake into bite-sized pieces. Layer cake, gelatine mix, cake, gelatine mix, etc. Chill. Mix other package Dream Whip and spread on cake. Top with coconut.

title: linda's fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour and cornmeal. Put in shaker or dish; add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle on tomatoes and cover both sides well. Put in frying pan on medium heat in cooking oil.
Cook on each side
until brown. Brown slowly.

title: carrot fish sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add carrot, marjoram and thyme.
Add squirt of wine.
Add fish and bouillon cube.
Cook 1/2 hour on low flame.
Add water if needed.

title: caviar pie
directions: Sieve eggs and mix with butter.
Spread in a glass serving dish, covering sides and bottom.
Chill thoroughly.
Add alternate layers of onions and caviar.
Spread sour cream over caviar. Sprinkle parsley around edges.
Serve with crackers and small rye bread slices.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease 1 qt baking dish well.
Preheat oven to 350°. Dissolve cornstarch in water and mix all ingredients.
Top with cinnamon and a few slices of oleo.
Bake 1 hour uncovered.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat egg.
Add dry ingredients, butter and milk.
Add nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach sausage cheese pie
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients. Place in an uncooked pie shell.
Top with second crust.
Cut a hole the size of a quarter in top crust.
Brush top crust with egg yolk. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: cmp cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter, flour and 3/4 cup nuts in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: toasted corned beef
directions: Spread on party rye bread and toast.
A favorite with men! Also delicious with tomato soup.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, pepper and salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Boil mustard seed, vinegar and celery seed 1 minute.
Let cool.
Blanch cabbage before freezing.
Add second mixture to the first mixture, then freeze.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook about 6 or 7 hours on high setting.
Add sour cream before serving.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a bowl, whip together cream cheese and mayonnaise with an electric mixer on medium speed. Add onions, tomatoes, Worcestershire, salt and lemon juice, then whip with an electric mixer on medium for 1 minute.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve cold.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mini cheese and bacon bagels
directions: Mix mayonnaise, bacon and cheese together.
Split bagels in half.
Spread mixture on bagel halves.
Cook in broiler 5 minutes and serve.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Combine the vegetables together.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours, stirring at least once an hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream together the sugar and crisco. Add a beaten egg and mix well. Then add the yeast mixture, mix well. Add the remaining 2 cups of hot water and the salt. Mix in the flour until the dough kneads without sticking to the work surface. Let it rise, covered, in a warm place for at least 1 hour before baking. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 20-30 minutes.

title: refreshing fruit cup
directions: Mix fruit lightly in bowl; chill.
Serve in fruit dishes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put eggs in blender container; cover and blend until fluffy, about 5 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients in order given and blend about 5 seconds, or until potatoes are finely grated, not lumpy.
Bake on hot, greased griddle about 2 minutes on each side, using about 2 tablespoons batter for each.
Turn once.
Do not stack pancakes.
Serve with hot applesauce. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen pancakes.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix together and brown meatballs in hot oil.

title: mavis watson's bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt in large pan.
Pour several trays of ice over mixture and let set for 3 hours, then drain. Heat sugar, vinegar and spices.
Pour hot mixture over pickles in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Fill sterilized jars with pickles and pour hot liquid over pickles until full, then seal.

title: golden potato medley
directions: Cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Slice carrots.
Cover with boiling water and simmer until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until onion is tender.
Blend in flour and add milk.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat; add the pimento.
Stir in cheese until blended.
Turn cooked potatoes and carrots into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce and stir lightly.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lunch box squares
directions: *Buttermilk:
To 1 teaspoon vinegar, add milk to make 1/2 cup.

title: piccadillo
directions: Brown, drain and crumble beef.
Chop and saute vegetables (onion, pepper and garlic) in olive oil.
Add beef and remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over white rice or fry potatoes, cut in 1/2-inch lengths and add to mixture.

title: chinese wedding cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add water and simmer until rice is tender.
Place in casserole dish. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and then cheese. Serve with taco chips.
Easy and very good!

title: chocolate custard devil's food cake
directions: Combine chocolate, 1/2 cup milk, whole egg and 2/3 cup sugar; cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Cream shortening and remaining cup of sugar; add egg yolks and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup milk and vanilla extract. Stir in chocolate custard mixture.
Bake in 2 waxed paper-lined 8-inch layer cake pans in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put layers together with frosting of your choice (regular white seven minute frosting, ivory frosting or chocolate fudge frosting).

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Take juice of 1 orange and add enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Then add 3 tablespoons melted margarine, add rind of grated orange.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup chopped raw cranberries.
Pour into well-greased bread pan and let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti noodles in green box mix and additional package. Rinse. Simmer meat, onion, 1/2 green pepper, spices and both spice mixes from green box mix (Parmesan and spice packet). Drain. Add tomatoes, green pepper, cheese, margarine and water and simmer until combined. Add to drained spaghetti and simmer until combined.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix egg, broccoli, cottage cheese and milk in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put Jiffy mix on top and bake at 375° to 400°, until done.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Let set 5 minutes; add to milk mixture and add 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and stir well, then add remaining flour to make a soft dough; knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Shape like jelly roll.
Cut for caramel rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Shape in balls; roll out and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: lite pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: In 1 quart casserole, combine green onion, garlic and butter. Microwave at High for 30 to 60 seconds until butter melts.
Add cream cheese.
Microwave at High 45 to 90 seconds to soften cream cheese.
Mix in remaining ingredients, chill overnight.

title: steak and rice
directions: In large skillet, cut up mushrooms and saute.
Cut up onion and saute; cut up pepper and saute.
Cut up steak and saute.
Pour in tomatoes and simmer for a while.
In a saucepan, prepare white rice.
Then serve mixture over rice.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until tender. Drain and cool. Mix with onion and bell pepper. Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over vegetables and store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake as directed in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder two or three times.
Combine wet with dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts.
Add carrots, small amount at a time.
Bake at 350° on sheet cake pan or in layers for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, milk and oil. Beat until smooth. Put in greased pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green chiffon salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
When mixture begins to congeal, add other ingredients. Place in mold to jell.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend together sugar, flour, soda, and cocoa.
Add water, vanilla, and mayonnaise.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Does not make good layer cake.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine mix, jello, water, oil and strawberries until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° until done (about 25 minutes).
Makes 3 layers.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put both cans of cherry pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over cherry pie filling and gently pat down.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.
Serve warm or cool.

title: squash bread
directions: Put cut squash in food processor.
Process until consistency is as small as possible; add 4 eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix in chopped walnuts at end.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for 1 hour.

title: sugar and nut glazed brie
directions: In a small jar, stir sugar, nuts and brandy.
Cover and chill up to 1 week or can be frozen up to 6 months.

title: easy zucchini lasagna
directions: Mix first three ingredients in bowl.
May add cooked hamburg or sausage to this mixture.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of lasagna pan.
Spread ricotta cheese on noodles and layer next. Sprinkle zucchini, mozzarella and parmesan cheese next.
Repeat process (usually three layers) ending with sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in small amount of chicken fat or margarine.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put in half of cooked spaghetti.
Add 1/2 peppers, onion, celery and half of chicken.
Spread with 1 cup of soup.
Repeat the layers. Cover with grated cheese.
Spoon 3 to 4 tablespoons of chicken stock over top to moisten.
Slivered almonds may be sprinkled over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen before baking. Cover with foil.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Put eggs, vinegar and sugar in double boiler (high heat), beating constantly with hand mixer.
As soon as thick and smooth, remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
When cold, fold in marshmallows and fruit cocktail (drained) and whipped cream. Chill 24 hours.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter and spread into bottom of 9x13 pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Blend pudding and milk and spread on top.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Put
cucumbers
in wide mouth jars.
Soak in salt water that will
float
an egg, 14 days.
Do not trim ends of cucumbers. Take
out
of
salt
water, wash good and slice.
Cover with water;
add alum and soak overnight.
Cover with vinegar. Soak
6 hours.
Drain
vinegar
off good.
Using 10 pounds of sugar,
pack in big mouth jars or containers, putting layer of pickles;
layer of sugar; adding pickling spices all along, as much
as
you like.
Cover containers with wax paper or Saran Wrap,
then
put lid
on.
Do not seal tight.
The sugar will melt and cover with juice.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg, then add dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed, then let cool.
Make up 1 box strawberry jello mix as directed; let cool.
Drip the jello mix into the cake by a teaspoon in a row across the cake.
Use Cool Whip as icing.

title: zucchini casserole pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 10-inch pie plate or 2-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil, cheese, baking mix, parsley flakes, black pepper and garlic powder; mix well.
Add zucchini, onion and jalapenos; stir until zucchini is just coated with batter.
Pour mixture into a baking dish and bake 40 to 50 minutes, or until lightly brown and puffy.
Cut and serve as an appetizer or main dish with salad and bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and tuna.
Add remaining ingredients and mold into 2 small or 1 large ball.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in Bisquick mix and oatmeal.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoonful onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Lightly
cool and transfer to wire racks to finish cooling.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: polenta gnocchi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare polenta (see Polenta recipe) with Parmesan cheese; add salt, cayenne pepper and nutmeg to taste.
With moistened hands, form polenta into 2-inch rounds or ovals.
Place them in single layer in greased shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and butter.
Bake Gnocchi for 30 minutes or until puffed and heated through.
Place under preheated broiler for 2 minutes or until golden.
Delicious plain or with a light tomato and basil sauce.

title: grandma's cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl; add melted butter last.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix altogether with 1 or 2 cans of Eagle Brand milk.
Mix in a tube pan and press.
Put in refrigerator for 2 days before dumping.

title: vegie garden pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet, pressing edges together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Let cool.
Mix the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix in a bowl until smooth.
Spread over the cooled crescent roll crust.
Top with your favorite fresh vegetables. Chill and cut into squares.
Be sure you press the vegetables firmly into the cheese base.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Place batter in a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Number of servings: 24.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Pour cold egg nog into a bowl.
Add pudding, rum and nutmeg. With electric mixer at low speed, beat until blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with remaining topping.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg.

title: baked curried fruit
directions: *Can drain all these into a common pitcher to make a juice drink.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash tender.
Drain.
Mix with next 6 ingredients. Place in baking dish with bread crumbs on top and cheese on the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown as desired.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Add jello to boiling water; cool slightly and add sherbet. Mix well; add pineapple and oranges.
Congeal.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in the center. Add eggs, bananas, pineapple, nuts, oil and vanilla.
Stir, but do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Do not use mixer!

title: perked cranapple tea
directions: Mix ingredients in 35 cup percolator. In basket of percolator put 1/2 box whole cloves and 6 to 8 cinnamon sticks.

title: beef tomato
directions: Cut
beef
into
bite
size chunks.
In a bowl, combine shoyu, ginger and sugar.
Add beef; marinate for 1 hour.
In a pot,
add oil
and heat.
Add beef;
cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Set
aside. Place onion, celery and green pepper in pot for 2 minutes.	Stir cornstarch into remaining sauce.
Add marinated beef
and tomatoes
to vegetables; mix well.	Cook for 3 minutes.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Tear biscuits open and roll out each piece.
Cut sweet potatoes in 1/4 inch thick slices, use potatoes 1 1/2 inches in diameter and put 2 slices stacked upon rolled out biscuit.
Fold biscuit together and press edges together.
Melt margarine in baking dish and dip both sides of biscuit and lay in margarine.
Mix sugar and water and bring to boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Use 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix lightly; let set a couple of hours in refrigerator. Serve.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Cut fish into cubes.
Cook the celery, green pepper, onion and garlic powder in oil until pepper is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and add this with tomatoes, okra and spices to the oil.
Simmer for 30 minutes and add the fish and cook until it is done.
Serve with rice in bowls.
Add pepper sauce to taste.

title: refreshing fruit plate
directions: Dressing:
Combine cottage cheese, banana and orange juice in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add applesauce with soda mixed in it.
Sift together flour and spices and add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs, then nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into greased floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn onto clean towel and cool completely.
Sift powdered sugar on top or drizzle with glaze.

title: bet's goulash
directions: Brown meat and put to one side of pan.
Brown chopped onions in one side of pan and mix.
Add tomatoes and juice (mash before adding).
Pour in beans, noodles, tomatoes and chilies and celery soup.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cheese last.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take off heat and cover until cheese melts.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and bananas; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with the dry.
Stir in vanilla.

title: chocolate cream cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, chocolate, brown sugar, granulated sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Chill dough if soft. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake just until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: grampa's snow cream
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and add snow and more snow until it becomes thick.
Add food coloring if desired.
Besides tasting good, it's not a bad way to get rid of some of that snow that comes our way in the winter.

title: orange cookies
directions: Sift
together
flour,
salt and soda.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Combine
eggs and orange peel into sugar mixture. Add flour
mixture
alternately
with 1/2 cup of orange juice until well
blended.
Add nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix and press into pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with foil.
Lay cut-up chicken side by side in pan.
Mix together the ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: flora raper's favorite 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Blend well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift 3 times.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Pour into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: warm apple dessert crepes
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Brush a small frying pan with oil, heat it but not to smoking.
Add 2 tablespoons batter and tilt the pan to cover bottom with batter.
Lightly brown on one side, then cook for a few seconds on the other side.
Slide onto a saucer and stack with waxed paper in between.
Makes 14 to 16 crepes.
May be frozen.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoon water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, sugar, lemon juice and juice from pineapple.
Let stay in refrigerator for 15 minutes or more, until syrupy.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and stir over low heat until thickened and smooth.
Add cheese and lemon juice, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add chicken and sauce to rice; mix well.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: olive cheese balls(serves 36)
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in melted margarine; mold 1 teaspoon of this dough around each olive and shape into a ball.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Bake in 400° preheated oven until set (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: fruit dip
directions: Prepare fruit of your choice.
Keep fruit in 7-Up until ready to use to retain color and give a sweeter taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soups together. Put rice in 2-quart casserole dish. Pour soups over rice. Arrange chicken breasts on top of rice. Sprinkle onion soup over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips, pecans and milk last. (These are also delicious if you add 1 cup butterscotch chips.)
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add rest of ingredients to meat. Mix well, then simmer on low for 20 minutes.

title: special bacon cheese dog
