directions: Cook hot dog, then spread pizza sauce on the bun before you place the hot dog on the bun.
Layer the bacon directly over the bun, so the cheese will cover everything.
Place cheese on bacon. Wrap in paper towel and heat in microwave for 1 minute on Low.

title: anne's roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On a floured surface, roll rolls into 7x 5-inch rectangle, arrange ham and cheese slices on rectangle.
Cut ham and cheese to fit, leaving 1/2-inch of dough all the way around.
Spread filling with mustard, brush rim of dough with egg. Fold dough and filling over so 5-inch sides meet, with fork, seal edges.
Place on cookie sheet, brush with leftover egg.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter together.
Add melted mixture to cereal.
Put powdered sugar in plastic bag. Shake until all pieces are covered.
Chill.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Work butter in a bowl until creamy.
Stir in sugar and flour; mix well.
Add syrup and eggs.
Beat until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and salt.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°. Continue to bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until center is firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: asparagus in sauce mimosa
directions: Cover eggs with water in a small saucepan and set on high heat. When the water comes to a rolling boil, turn off the heat and let the eggs set in the water until they are cool enough for you to handle them. Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add salt to taste. Cut off the bottom 1 to 1 1/2-inches of the asparagus. Peel the asparagus, starting very lightly at the tip and gradually increasing pressure towards the base. Boil the asparagus just until tender enough that a knife slides in easily, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from hot water to a pan of cold water to stop the cooking. When almost ready to serve, shell the hard-cooked eggs and separate the whites from the yolks. Chop separately as fine as possible and them combine them in a mixing bowl (chopped them together smears the yolks). Add the parsley, mixed herbs, lemon juice and vinegar and stir together. Stir in the olive oil. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, then taste and add more if necessary. Pat the asparagus dry and arrange it on a platter. Spoon the dressing on top in a swatch pattern across the middle of the spears. Serve at room temperature. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Allow yogurt to thaw slightly, and add thawed strawberries and red soda.
Serve immediately.

title: almond bars
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler; stir in peanuts, peanut butter, Rice Krispies and almond extract.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Spread evenly and let stand about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken scaloppine with lemon
directions: Place the chicken pieces between two pieces of wax paper or plastic wrap and pound with the flat side of a mallet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Coat the chicken with flour and shake off the excess.
In a wide frying pan, over medium-high heat, place butter and oil.
When butter melts, add as many pieces as will fit without crowding and cook quickly just until the meat is no longer pink when slashed, about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Place on a hot platter and keep warm.
Cook remaining pieces, adding more butter and oil if needed; add to platter and keep warm.

title: blueberry batter cake
directions: Place blueberries in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Blend together the shortening, sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour this batter over the blueberries.
Sprinkle batter with mixture of sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, cook chicken.
Remove chicken when done and chop up.
Take 4 cups of chicken broth (add water, if necessary to make 4 cups).
Add:
onion, garlic, chili powder, cumin, zucchini, carrots, celery, chicken and chicken noodle soup. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook hamburger and diced onion until done, crumbling it as it cooks.
Strain off all juices and return to pan.
Add ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Simmer on low heat until warm.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate with butter just until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, salt and eggs with hand beater or whisk.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until filling is puffed.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort beans and rinse well; cover with tap water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and place in a large, heavy pot.
Add hot water, ham bone, onion, green onion, garlic, bay leaf, cayenne and salt.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender, adding more water, if necessary, to keep from sticking.
Stir often.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend the oleo, salt, nutmeg and lemon flavoring.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Drop with teaspoon; flatten with glass covered with damp cloth dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Combine wheat biscuits, butter, honey and salt.
Add water and cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to biscuit mixture.
Stir in flour with heavy spoon or spatula.
Don't knead. Place in two loaf pans.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: oatmeal chocolate drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg and add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate morsels.
Drop by rounded half-teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Using a tube pan, spray with Pam.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom, set aside.
Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, water, oil and 1/2 cup rum together.
Spread over pecans in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Grate 1 cup each kind of cheese. Set aside 1/4 cup of each for top.
Mix eggs, add cottage cheese, Jack and Cheddar cheese, crackers and chili.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (covered).
Then top with both cheeses (1/4 cup each), leave uncovered.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting.

title: francesca's shrimp and shells picatta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in large preheated skillet or pot, add olive oil and saute shrimp, peppers, mushrooms, scallions and garlic.
Cook for 5 to 6 minutes or until shrimp is cooked.
Add wine, lemon juice, capers and butter.
Blend well and cook for 1 minute.
Toss hot pasta into pot and mix thoroughly.
Add parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green beans with bacon and potatoes
directions: String the beans and break into pieces if they are very large. You may wish to leave very young tender beans whole. Fry bacon pieces for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Pour out grease.
Add onion and fry 10 minutes longer.
Mix together the bacon, onion, beans, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add broth. Clean the potato skins; do not peel. Arrange over beans. Cover tightly and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add more broth, if needed.

title: *custard baked in phyllo dough
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, eggs, farina, sugar and the 4 tablespoons butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil and is thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

Place half of the filo pastry in a 12 x 16-inch baking pan, buttering each sheet before placing it in the pan. Pour filling into pan and cover with remaining filo, again brushing each one generously with butter.
With a sharp knife, cut top pastry square shaped pieces and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown. Remove from oven and pour the syrup.

title: mom's fruit dip
directions: Blend strawberry cream cheese with Marshmallow Creme.
Serve with sliced apples, pears, strawberries or any kind of fruit desired.

title: taco casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion and garlic into large skillet; cook until meat is brown.
Drain.
Combine meat mixture, tomato sauce, water and seasonings in a medium bowl; mix well.
Place 1/2 of meat into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of kidney beans; sprinkle with 1/2 of corn chips.
Repeat layers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes longer. Top with lettuce.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to milk mixture and blend well.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and a dash of nutmeg.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and salt.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in melted butter and vanilla.
Add pecans.
A few whole pecans may be used for decoration.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 50 minutes.
A knife inserted comes out clean when baked.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Butter tube pan heavily and place frozen rolls in pan.
In saucepan, melt butter and pour over rolls.
Combine dry pudding, cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over top of rolls.
Let stand, uncovered, overnight.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Invert on plate and serve.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes(a farm journal recipe)
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain. Combine potatoes, sour cream, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Beat with electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed until light and fluffy.

title: skinny soup
directions: Cook altogether for about 2 hours.
Add 1 can green beans. Simmer 1 more hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients; simmer.
Cook noodles; drain.
Layer noodles, beef mixture and cheese; repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Use a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth bag and bring to a boil in the water.
Add tea.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices.
Add juices and sugar; stir well.

title: minestrone
directions: Cook bacon in 4-quart saucepot 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until onion is tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, veggies, macaroni and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook 12 minutes.
Stir in beans and cook 2 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan.

title: sour cream
directions: Place cheese in large sieve to drain thoroughly.
Put in blender with milk.
Blend until mixture is the consistency of sour cream.
Yields 24 (2 Tbsp.) servings.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Place
in	a Dutch oven or large saucepan with next	8 ingredients.	Simmer, covered, for 2	hours or until meat is tender, breaking up tomatoes with a spoon.
Add chickpeas
or
red	kidney beans and heat about 5 minutes.	Serve with Premium crackers, unsalted tops.
Makes 8 (1 3/4 cups) servings.

title: beet-rhubarb compote
directions: Wrap each beet in aluminum foil. Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Cook the rhubarb according to directions.
Dice cooked beets. Add to the cooked rhubarb.
Chill. Serve as side dish. It's colorful with a different taste.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Line a Pyrex baking dish with the chicken and broccoli. Combine the cream of chicken or golden mushroom soup, 1/3 cup of mayonnaise and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice. Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy buttercream mints
directions: Beat butter, cream and 5 cups of sugar in an electric mixer at medium speed.
Beat in egg white.
Add remaining sugar and more if needed to make consistency of cookie dough.
Add oil of peppermint to taste. Add food coloring.
Blend until evenly flavored and colored.
Work with about half of the mixture at a time.
Roll with a rolling pin between 2 sheets of wax paper to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds with cutter or twist cap bottle.
Reroll scraps and cut.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt and gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine ingredients. Flour to roll out. Cut out cookies and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients (only 2 of the eggs).
Add Miracle Whip to taste; put sliced eggs on top and sprinkle with paprika.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, then add oil.
Beat.
Add cake flour, cinnamon, salt and apples.
Bake in large pan at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Optional:
One half cup each of raisins and nuts.

title: pineapple-pecan cheese ball
directions: Spread nuts in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes or until toasted; cool.
Coarsely chop 1 cup of the toasted nuts.
Set aside.
Chop the remaining nuts until ground.
In a food processor bowl, combine ground nuts, cream cheese, pineapple, red pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Process or beat until well blended.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Shape into one large ball or divide in half and shape into small balls.
Roll in coarsely chopped nuts.
Wrap and chill until serving time.
(Or wrap and freeze for up to a month.
Thaw 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.)
Serve with crackers and/or fresh vegetable pieces.
Makes 3 cups.

title: swiss cheese and crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange cheese evenly over bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle in onions then crab meat.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel and dry mustard; pour evenly over crab meat.
Top with sliced almonds and a sprinkle of cheese.
Cook in slow 325° oven for 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together to make a batter.
Dip each piece of chicken in the above mixture and roll in corn flakes or cracker crumbs.
Makes enough batter for two chickens cut up. Bake 1 hour at 400° or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs (beaten well). Stir in corn and milk.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 325° for 45 minutes.
Stir once, before it starts to set.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables (thawed and drained) with soup, 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, sour cream, pimento, pepper and 1/2 can onion rings. Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: fruit roll ups
directions: Cut up and blend fruit until pureed.
Sweeten with honey or corn syrup to taste.
Line a baking tray with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Tape to all four sides.
Spread pureed fruit evenly, leaving a one-inch border.
Bake at 150° until fruit feels leather like, pliable and no sticky spots in center.
Remove from tray while warm and roll up.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cream shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Blend until creamy. Blend in eggs. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture gradually. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: easy chocolate chip chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put oil in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Tip pan to coat bottom and sides with oil.
Add first four ingredients and water.
Stir with a fork until well blended. Scrape sides of pan with a spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: beans and tomatoes
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the garlic and sage; saute.
Add the tomatoes and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
Add the beans, cover and cook over very low heat for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. The finished dish should have the consistency of a soup.

title: sausage cheese casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Layer bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread sausage evenly over bread, then layer cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard and pour over cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna fish spread
directions: Melt cheese and salad dressing in the top of a double boiler. Remove from range and stir in tuna.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate pies (2)
directions: Mix all together. Beat good. Pour in unbaked pie shells. Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad in pita pockets
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl except for pitas.
Warm the pitas in oven.
Cut in half and open the pockets.
Fill each pocket with chicken salad.

title: homemade catsup
directions: Mix in large pan.
Cook to a small rolling boil until thick.

title: taylor's brownies
directions: Beat softened butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add vanilla and salt, mix, then add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts with a big spoon.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Press butter and cookies into a pie plate.
Add filling and sprinkle cookies on top.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue beef
directions: In skillet, combine onion, pepper and carrot with oil.
Stir until tender.
Crumble beef on top and cook until no longer pink. Stir in barbecue sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins for about 1 1/2 hours or until done. Peel potatoes when cooled off into a large bowl.
Chop celery, onions and eggs into the bowl of peeled potatoes.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and sandwich spread.
Mix together.
Add pepper, Lawry's seasoned salt, sugar, onion salt and garlic salt and mix.
Make it thick and not too soft.
Taste and add more of the seasonings if needed.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Whisk eggs and stir in the rest.
Top with 1/4 cup nuts, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, milk and bread crumbs together.
Roll into balls and line into baking dish.

title: parmesan pan biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Coat a 9-inch square baking pan with butter.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except milk. Stir in milk just until moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 10 times or until smooth.
Roll dough into 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cut into twelve 1-inch strips.
Place each strip into pan coated with butter, turning once.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Fill a pastry-lined pie pan with rhubarb.
Sprinkle generously with sugar, which has been combined with flour.
Sprinkle jello over sugar and flour.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust or with strips of pastry.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: real corny bread
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix juice and Southern Comfort and chill.
Add chilled 7-Up last with orange slices and ice ring.
Serves 25.

title: french onion soup
directions: To a large pot add onions (peeled and thinly sliced) and butter.
Saute 8-10 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Add broth, worcestershire sauce and wine.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: easy swedish meat balls
directions: Combine and roll into balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion and then drain.
Add soups and enchilada sauce with green chilies into meat and onion.
Mix well and simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer baking dish with meat sauce, cheese and folded tortillas.
Repeat layering.
Bake the dish at 325° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with egg white.
In a bag, mix bread crumbs, spaghetti mix and garlic, then put chicken in the bag and shake.
Put chicken in an 8 x 12-inch dish and bake uncovered for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake uncovered an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift into an 8-inch greased pan all the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Make 3 holes in the flour mixture. In one hole, put the melted butter.
In next hole, put the vanilla and in last hole, put the vinegar.
Over all, pour the warm water. Stir with a fork.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, baking powder, salt and 2 cups flour. Use other 2 cups flour on fruit and nuts. Hand mix and bake in tube pan at 225° for 3 hours.

title: banana-blueberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, blend first six ingredients; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to batter; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place chips on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ground beef, then grated cheese.
Mix beans, soup and tomatoes; pour on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon.
Chop or crumble bacon; save 3 or 4 strips for top.
Mix everything together in large bowl.
Pour mix into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes during baking time.
Garnish with strips of bacon and serve hot.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to boil. Add peanuts and coloring. Cook over medium heat until hard-boil stage (250° on candy thermometer) about 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from flame. Add margarine and salt. Beat until mixture is quite thick and creamy. Drop in clusters on wax paper or greased cookie sheet. If mixture hardens too rapidly, put back on stove on low heat a few minutes. Stir well, then continue dropping.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut up the chicken and season generously with salt, pepper and cayenne. In a heavy pot, fry the chicken in oil until golden brown. Remove the oil and reserve it for making the roux.
Add the onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic to the chicken. Cover and cook over low heat.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container. To serve,
add 1 level teaspoon of the mix to a 6-ounce cup of boiling water.
May
be
kept
unrefrigerated
for up to three months in an airtight container.

title: chicken and dumplins]
directions: Cook chicken in pot of water.
Flatten biscuits with rolling pin (hands).
Flour them, then tear them apart and put into chicken.
Add all other ingredients at same time.
Cook until juice is thick enough for you and dumplings are done.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables to boiling liquid and cook until vegetables change color.
Put into jars and seal.

title: devil's food squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to boiling point.
Pour over next 2 ingredients.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix the potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine (melted), salt, onion soup, sour cream, cheese (except 1/4 cup) and ham.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.

title: mandarin chicken with noodles
directions: Cut chicken into strips and cook as for stir-fry. When done, remove from skillet or wok.
Break Oriental noodles into bite size pieces (set aside flavor packet).
Combine noodles, water, zucchini slices, sliced celery and minced garlic. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until noodles are done and vegetables tender.
Stir in cooked chicken, flavor packet, sweet and sour sauce and peanuts.
Top each serving with orange sections.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; stir in flour until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Spread in an ungreased jelly roll pan (large flat).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with a little milk.
Add pudding and rest of milk.
Beat until thick.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup before serving. Refrigerate.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into French fry strips.
Boil until done.
Pour about half of liquid off and add margarine, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add just enough flour to thicken.

title: cherry deluxe
directions: Mix together milk and pudding until smooth.
Then add Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften ice cream.
Mix ice cream, peanut butter and Cool Whip. Pile into graham cracker crusts and place in freezer.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.
Also delicious with chocolate pie crusts.

title: thai rice with chicken, cashew nuts and dried chilies
directions: Press the cooked rice into a wet ring mold.
Remove to serving plate.
Heat the oil in the frying pan. Fry the dried chilies, cut with scissors and set aside.
Using the leftover oil, fry the chicken and onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and m.s.g.
Keep turning until light brown.
Add chopped celery, black mushroom, fish sauce, soy sauce and chicken broth.
Cover.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the cornstarch.
Stir until thickened.
Add cashew nuts and turn over lightly.
Spoon into center of the rice.
Top with dried chili and garnish with lemon, tomato and coriander leaves.
Serve.

title: hot mild cider
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with orange wedge on each cup.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat in grated zucchini.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Blend into zucchini mixture.
Add nuts. Turn into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Have cheese and ham at room temperature.
Add all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix until well blended with mixer. Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with party crackers.

title: our favorite baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Drain.
Place onion, celery, green pepper, pork and beans, catsup, molasses, brown sugar and Tabasco in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Mix well.
Top with the strips of bacon. Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut off top of bread and hollow out.
Mix dip ingredients; pour into bread shell.
Scatter chunks of bread around dip-filled shell to serve.

title: beef and bean round-up
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
In baking dish, mix beans and tomatoes with juice; spread evenly.
In a medium bowl combine ground beef, potato flakes, onion, catsup, egg, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon granules, mustard, pepper and garlic powder.
Shape into 24 meatballs.

Arrange meatballs in three rows of eight over the beans, allowing space between rows. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes or until edges are boiling. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, stir baking mix, cheese and milk until baking mix is moistened.
Remove baking dish from oven.
Drop dough by tablespoons in two rows of eight between meatballs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients in a 3 quart electric ice cream freezer can.
Freeze.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Stir up. Pour into a well oiled baking pan. Bake at 425 degrees until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Combine mushroom soup, water chestnuts (drained) and butter in saucepan; cook for 10 minutes on low heat.
Put layer of broccoli in baking dish, top with 1/2 soup mixture and 1/2 cheese, then another layer of broccoli and finish with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add onion rings and brown lightly.

title: taco guacamole dip
directions: Spread bean dip on plate. Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, and Taco seasoning and spread on bean dip. Add avocados, tomatoes, onion, and olives to the top. Serve with taco chips.

title: savory southern eggplant
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Add onion, pepper, eggplant, tomato and seasonings to bacon fat.
Cook until tender.
Fold in cheese.
Place in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bacon. Brown under broiler for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: barbecued black beans and rice
directions: *I used either Italian or Cajun style stewed tomatoes and Green Giant Mexicorn.

title: veggie dip
directions: Spread 4 large slices of bologna or minced ham with softened cream cheese seasoned with onions or chives and mustard.
Place slices together (like a layer cake).
Spread cheese over top and sides; decorate with sliced olives.
Chill.
Cut into wedges.

title: bill's mushroom chicken
directions: Wash chicken and season.
Brown chicken on both sides; drain cooking oil.
Add sherry, soup and onion soup.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients to make firm dough.
Roll thin, cut and bake.
May also be used as drop cookies.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Cover with foil and bake until bubbly.
When casserole is about done, top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted margarine, mixed.
Leave foil off and continue to bake until lightly brown.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Pour beef stew into 2-quart casserole dish. Mix next 6 ingredients together and pour on top of the beef stew. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: waldorf stew
directions: Put roast, onions, celery, carrots and potatoes in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add tomato soup to mixture and rinse can with a little water.
Cover with lid and cook 5 hours at 250°.
Do not raise lid.
Do not brown meat; makes its own gravy.

title: stained glass windows
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in pan.
Cool, then add marshmallows and pecans.
Divide into 3 parts and form 3 logs in plastic wrap.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, cut into slices.

title: microwave potatoes(dinner for 4)
directions: Rinse and pat dry potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and add your choice of herbs.

title: pat in pan pie crust
directions: Mix and pat in pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and tear lettuce.
Place in bowl with onion.
Put remaining ingredients in skillet, bringing to a boil.
Pour dressing over lettuce and onion.
Serve warm.

title: irish tea cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Sift and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and raisins. Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in regular funnel cake pan.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add applesauce and raspberries.
Make small balls of the cream cheese.
Roll in nuts and place in bottom of mold.
Put a small amount of Jell-O mix over cheese balls. Refrigerate until set.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture. Chill until set.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream, margarine and sugar.
Stir in Jiffy mix and corn.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes or until firm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook 4 minutes on high.
Add peanuts and cook 3 more minutes on high. Add butter and vanilla, stir well.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more or until peanuts are lightly browned and syrup is hot.
Add baking soda and stir gently until foamy, use wooden spoon.
Spread evenly on greased baking sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: apricot chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, mix apricot preserves, onion soup mix and Catalina dressing.
Place chicken in foil-lined baking dish. Spread mixture over top of chicken evenly.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple prune coffee cake
directions: In a medium-sized mixing bowl, beat together butter, eggs, orange extract and apple juice.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and spices; beat well.
Stir in diced prunes and nuts.
Spoon into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well and make into balls the size of a marble.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
These can be made up and frozen.
Will take longer baking time if just out of the freezer.

title: dilly cucumber salad
directions: Mix sour cream, garlic, sugar, salt and dill weed.
Stir in cucumbers. Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: cold shrimp with spicy sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp and use as a dip or sauce for the shrimp.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all
together and place in oblong pan.
(Will freeze well.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, brown sugar and sugar until creamy, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until mixed well.
Scrape bowl.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and chopped nuts, if you'd like.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple-a-luau
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, syrup and butter in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add baking soda and pour over popped corn.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet and bake one hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: product 19 candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix until it is blended well.
Add Product 19 cereal and drop by teaspoon on buttered pans or wax paper.
Yields about 65.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Toss together the first 6 ingredients. Bring the olive oil, vinegar, salt, sugar, black pepper and garlic to a boil. Cool 5 minutes.
Mix vegetables and cooled sauce.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours to marinate.
Better after 2 days.
Bring to room temperature before serving.

title: grape salad
directions: Clean the grapes.
Drain juice of pineapple chunks and save. Beat the egg; set aside.
Mix 1 cup of pineapple juice with 1 cup of sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add cornstarch and heat over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over grapes.
Add pineapple chunks and nuts.
Mix together. Refrigerate until needed.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Add cream of tartar, soda, salt, creamed shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks and beat.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
On greased, floured pan, drop by rounded teaspoon and smooth lightly (use wet spoon).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Place cheese in mixing bowl.
Mash with fork until it is pliable.
Add clams.
Mix well.
Add clam juice until desired consistency.
Serve chilled.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients; put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add marshmallows and sprinkle with grated coconut; brown just before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and toss with apples.
Place apple mixture into pie dish lined with pie crust.
Brush edges of crust with milk.
Lay pastry for upper crust.
Trim edges and flute.
Pierce with fork for steam vents.
Sprinkle top crust with cinnamon-sugar mix.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and salt.
Mix the flour, sugar and butter; sprinkle over the rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook beef over medium-high heat, stirring often until brown and crumbly.
Drain excess fat.
Add scallions and cook for 3 more minutes.
Stir in vegetables and undiluted soups; mix well.
Top with Tater Tops arranging evenly over beef mixture.
Bake about 35 minutes or until bubbly and potatoes are crisp and browned.

title: cream jellie
directions: Boil the gulaman in water in a covered pan until dissolved. Add milk, sugar and vanilla. Stir together until well mixed. Pour into mold and set aside to cool. Chill until firm. Serve as snack or light dessert.

title: white tassle hamburgers
directions: Combine dry onion and hot water in a cup and let stand for 10 minutes to soften.
In medium mixing bowl, combine ground round with the beef and add clear broth.
Shape the beef mixture into patties using 1/4 cup of meat mixture for each one.
Cut each hot dog bun into 2 equal pieces and cut off rounded ends.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in saucepan the flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add the oil, water and food coloring (optional).
Cook over medium heat for about three minutes or until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat and place the dough on a piece of waxed paper.
Knead slightly.
Store in an airtight container. This dough will keep for several weeks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip until thoroughly mixed.
Layer until all is used, usually 3 layers, ending with pudding.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in flour.
Add flavoring and pecans. Mix well.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing until well blended.
Mash 3/4 cup of strawberries.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in remaining strawberries.
Spoon into crust.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: quick easy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Add milk; cook stirring constantly until thick.
Add pumpkin, continue cooking, stirring constantly for about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cream the butter with the sugar. Blend into the creamed butter the eggs, one at a time. Combine the buttermilk or sour milk and vanilla. Add liquid alternately with the dry ingredients, beginning and ending with dry. Blend well into creamed mixture after each addition (low speed on mixer). Turn into 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan greased on bottom. Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes until cake springs back. Run spatula along edge and stem of pan. Prick cake with fork while still in pan. Pour sauce over. Cool before removing. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: beef barbecue bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bows until tender.
Drain.
In large skillet
cook meat with onion and pepper until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and add water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chow-chow
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain off. Add sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Put artichoke hearts in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Toss spinach with sour cream and soup mix.
Then stir in mushroom soup and the cheese.
Put this on top of the artichokes and top with the crumbled bacon.
Cook 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meat in butter; add all other ingredients and bake at 400° for 45 minutes in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: irish potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Place half of potatoes in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add half the sliced onion. Combine soup and milk.
Pour half over the onion and potatoes.
Top with remaining potato slices, onion slices and the soup mixture. Cover with plastic wrap, vent and microwave on High 20 to 25 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: amador gold cinnamon swirl
directions: Mix together the above and beat 5 to 10 minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Heat shortening until it melts. Add milk and heat until lukewarm.
Add sugar and yeast, stirring occasionally, until yeast dissolves.
Then add enough flour to make a batter about like cake batter.
Beat until smooth, cover and set in a warm place until doubled in size.
Stir down, add salt, soda, baking powder and enough flour to make a dough.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Press over bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: cream cheese coffeecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, flour and egg white until smooth.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place into ungreased 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Pour cheese mixture over crust. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is set and crust is deep golden brown.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: peppy chickpea diphouston, texas
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine garbanzo beans, yogurt, salad dressing, bread crumbs, lemon juice and red pepper. Cover and process until smooth.
Stir in olives.
Chill, uncovered, for at least one hour.
Serve with vegetable dippers or crackers.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: pork chops in ginger ale
directions: Saute onion in 1/8 cup butter until golden brown.
Place browned onions in a 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Brown chops in remaining 1/8 cup butter.
Place chops on top of onion in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Blend tomato puree with flour in a small bowl; add ginger ale and pour over chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: squirrel - cajun style
directions: Cut squirrels into 8 pieces each.
Season with salt and pepper. Melt margarine and fry squirrels until brown or start to stick to pot.
Add onions, bell peppers and garlic.
When vegetables are soft, add a small amount of cold water and Worcestershire sauce. Cover pot and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir well and add wine.
Cook until tender.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Can serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce and soda in bowl; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, then add applesauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix
butter and milk together in medium saucepan.
Heat to scalding.
Beat
eggs
slightly
and add sugar and vanilla. Stir into the milk and strain into a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven temperature down to
and
continue
baking for an additional 10 minutes. Brush
the
crust
with
unbeaten
egg
white before adding custard mixture.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Place a layer of each in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. The number of servings depends on size of dish.
One pound of hamburger in 1 1/2-quart casserole will serve 4.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in unsalted boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine eggs, soup and oregano in a bowl. Stir in tomatoes and broccoli.
Pour the mixture into a baking pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: margie's good punch
directions: You can use red Hawaiian Punch, ginger ale and red sherbet, like raspberry.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars on Low in microwave.
Remove candy from microwave and blend well with whipped topping.
Then place the mixture in the pie shell and refrigerate to firm.
Makes eight servings.

title: party carrot with crackers
directions: Beat cream cheese and cheddar for 1 minute.
Add carrot, peanuts, onion and dill - mix well.
Shape into a carrot.
Chill 2 hours - add parsley for top.
Serve with crackers.

title: festive sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine juice with ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce; stir to blend. Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add bell pepper and onion; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and juice mixture.
Cook, stirring until boils and thickens.
Add chicken and pineapple; heat through. Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 5.

title: beef brisket
directions: In a deep baking dish, add onion soup mix, chili sauce and Coke.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add beef.
Cover beef with mixture.
Cover dish with aluminum.
Bake about 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Chop onion, celery and green onions very fine.
Dissolve gelatin in water and set aside.
Heat soup and cream cheese until smooth.
Add gelatin.
Set aside until cool (about 30 minutes). When cool, add all other ingredients and stir.
Pour into mold. Let chill overnight.

title: chuck roast cooked in foil
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper.
Add dry onion soup mix and mushroom soup.
Wrap tightly in foil and place in baking dish. Bake at 325° for about 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli and half of the margarine. Place in casserole in layers with broccoli.

title: chocolate nut balls
directions: Form balls by mixing the first four ingredients.
Chill.
Then melt the chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip in the candy balls to coat with chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and melted butter, mixing well.
Press into bottom and 1 3/4 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, flour and salt, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into the prepared pan; bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool for 15 minutes.
Loosen from the sides of the pan with a spatula.
Cool 30 minutes. Remove from pan.
Spread topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients and place in refrigerator until chilled enough to form into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts and minced parsley.
Serves 25.

title: cranberry grilled chicken
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce, corn syrup, vinegar, corn oil, cinnamon and salt until well blended.
Grill chicken 6 inches from heat for 30 minutes, turning every so often.
Brush cranberry mixture on grilled chicken and cook for 15 to 20 minutes longer until chicken is tender.
Heat remaining cranberry mixture and serve with chicken.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onions, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff batter, beating well after each addition; cover.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Put first mixture into oblong pan.
Pour second mixture on top of first.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs well. Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well. Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in zucchini. Combine walnuts with 1 tablespoon flour; stir into batter.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans (bread pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on a wire rack.
Wrap tightly and let mellow overnight before slicing.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook water, sugar and white syrup until it spins like thread and is light brown.
Add peanuts.
When peanuts begin to pop, add butter, vanilla and soda.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and cool.
Break into pieces when cold.
This keeps well.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, rice and seasonings together.
Form into balls.
Brown in hot oil, turning frequently until light brown but not crusty.
Drain off oil or fat; add tomato sauce mixed with water.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken 'n sherry
directions: Make basic white sauce with butter, flour and cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over noodles.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll dough into small balls.
Bake at 350° until no imprint remains when cookie is touched.
Dip to coat in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup of water in a glass mixing bowl.
Microwave at High speed 2 to 3 minutes; stir until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut and pecans; put on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions; pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter; pour over batter.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let set 10 minutes.
Turn over onto a cookie sheet or tray.

title: key lime pie
directions: Prepare baked pastry shell or graham cracker crust as directed.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in Dairy Sweet and lime peel.
Gradually add lime juice, beating at medium speed until smooth and fluffy.
Turn beaten mixture into pie shell.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, top with whipped cream and garnish with lime slices, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: forever slaw
directions: Boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture while hot.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions using first 4 ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9-inch dish. When done, while still hot, pour Eagle Brand milk over cake (use fork to punch holes). Let cool a few minutes, then cover and put in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Remove. Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Place chicken and bay leaf in large pan.
Cover with salted water.
Boil until chicken is tender; cool.
Discard bay leaf. Debone and skin chicken; cut into bite-size pieces.
Reserve 1/4 cup broth.
Break spaghetti into thirds.
Cook in broth.
Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter; add spaghetti. Combine cream of mushroom soup and 1/4 cup reserved broth.
Stir into spaghetti mixture; add tomatoes and chicken.
Mix well.
Add seasonings; mix well.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan; spoon mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix ingredients in boiler.
Boil and stir until nuts absorb liquid.
Place on cookie sheet and roast in 300° oven.
After a few minutes in oven, loosen nuts on cookie sheet and shake often. Roast to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large bowl with fork, mix first 5 ingredients.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in bananas and eggs just until blended; spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: meat roll
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Add meat and mix well.
Pat mixture into 8 x 10-inch pan, lined with wax paper.

title: dirt cake dessert
directions: Cream
margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add pudding and milk;
mix
well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grind Oreos (use blender).
Layer
cookies
and pudding mix in flower pot, beginning and ending with cookies.	Chill 3 hours.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: For Sauce:
In small pan, stir together the milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in onion.

title: red and white delight salad
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Mix into gelatin the strawberries, drained pineapple and the bananas.
Add nuts if desired.
Place in flat pan in refrigerator until firm, reserving one-half for second layer at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over first layer.
Then add remaining mixture.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: plum jelly
directions: Mix Sure Jell and juice together.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add sugar all at once.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Pour jelly into hot jars.

title: aunt bea's company beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Boil noodles, drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and peppers.
Butter casserole dish, put half the noodles in it.
Cover with the cheese mixture.
Put the rest of noodles over the cheese mixture.
Pour over the melted butter. Put hamburger sauce over all this.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into mixture; add oatmeal, Krispies and coconut.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with a spoon.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces.
Mix together flour, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Combine milk and eggs.
Dip meat in egg and milk mixture and roll in bread crumbs. Brown meat in hot oil approximately 2 1/3 minutes each side for rare, 4 minutes each side for medium and 6 minutes each side for well-done.
Serves 6.

title: quick clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Add onion and cook until done.
Drain juice from clams and simmer juice in pan with onion and bacon.
In a large pot, add clams, potato soup and evaporated milk.
Add bacon-onion and juice mixture. Stir in thyme, pepper and Old Bay seasoning.
Mix and heat.
Don't boil.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes and remove from pans; let cool completely on wire racks.

title: royal icing
directions: Beat ingredients until light and fluffy and foam peaks.
Add more confectioners sugar, if needed, 1 Tbsp. at a time.
Store in air-tight container or cover with a damp cloth as it will dry quickly.

title: potato-onion bake
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan or skillet.
Add onion; cook over low heat, stirring, until onion is soft but not browned. Blend in flour; cook, stirring constantly, over low heat for 3 minutes, or until flour is thoroughly cooked.
Add one-third of the hot milk; stir vigorously while cooking sauce over medium heat until thickened and it begins to bubble.
Add remaining milk, thyme, bay leaf, salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and smooth.
Stir in grated cheese; heat until cheese has melted.
Strain through a fine sieve.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: steak bake
directions: Brown steak, salt and pepper.
Put into a baking dish.
Cover with 2 cups beef broth.
Add onion, rice and sliced tomato; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 quart of water and remaining ingredients.

title: snowbird trail bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together and add to first mixture.
Stir in oats, pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel heath cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cut slits randomly throughout cake.
Pour caramel in slits and all over the cake. Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Break up Heath bars and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sangria
directions: Dump the orange juice and lemonade into a very large container.
Follow the directions on the containers for reconstituting the juices but substitute the wine for the water. Add water or club soda to make 1 gallon.

title: smothered steak
directions: Trim steak and cut in serving pieces.
Salt and pepper; coat with
flour
on
both
sides.
Brown quickly in hot oil. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch shallow pan.
Do not have more than 2
layers. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice over
top. Sift
4 tablespoons flour over meat.
Pour boiling water over meat, be sure to moisten all the flour.
Cover with aluminum foil or	tight lid and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8 to 10. (Note:
deer meat can also be used.)

title: italian roast pepper salad
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the oil, garlic, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss well; chill completely.
Arrange in platter to serve.

title: warm broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water to cover for 1 minute.
Drain immediately and plunge into a bowl of ice water to stop cooking process.
Drain; pat dry.

title: lori's slush
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 15 minutes. Let cool. In blender mix bananas, orange juice and lemonade. Mix together with sugar water and vodka. Store in covered container in freezer. When serving fill water glass one-half full with syrup mixture, then add 7-Up or Squirt stirring as you go. Will not freeze solid because of vodka.

title: rich jam cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add flour. Divide into two balls.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Roll onto a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 2-inch diameter. Indent center with thumb and fill with 1/2 teaspoon jam.

title: hot pepper dish
directions: Chop fine green peppers, red peppers, hot peppers and onions. Cook everything for 20 minutes at rolling oil.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: kris kringle cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour that has been sifted, salt, oatmeal and chopped nuts, if desired.
Form into a roll; chill. After chilled, slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes, or until done.
You may freeze and use later the uncooked dough.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows and chill overnight.
Beat egg.
Add juice, flour, vinegar and sugar.
Cook until
thickened; chill overnight.

title: sugar free old fashion apple pie
directions: Preheat oven 425°. Prepare or buy a double pie crust and set one crust into a 9 inch pie pan. Place sliced apples into large bowl and set aside. Combine all dry ingredients in a small bowl. Sprinkle the mixture into apples and toss. Spoon apple mixture into crust. Place the second crust over the filling. Seal edges trim, and flute. Make small openings in the top of crust. Bake in a preheated oven until the top crust is golden brown about 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm or chilled. Makes 8 servings.

title: doggie delights
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet at 350°.
Refrigerate when cooled. Yields 25 delights.

title: vegetable minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, carrots and celery in oil.
Add hamburger (optional) and brown.
In a large kettle, combine all ingredients. Simmer until pasta is done.
Serve.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together until very smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour and milk alternately.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch layers.

title: fresh apricot almond tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 11-inch tart pan with pastry and refrigerate.
In a bowl, cream butter and sugar together. Stir in eggs, almonds, flour and vanilla.
Gradually pour rum or nectar into mixture, stirring constantly; pour into pastry-lined pan.
Arrange fresh apricots cut side down in tight circles over filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glorious mess
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Turn to low heat and cook 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir once or twice while cooking to prevent sticking.
Add water if needed, depending on the amount of liquid in the tomatoes and beans.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil giblets for stock.
Saute chopped onion and celery in butter until just done, not brown.
Crumble cornbread and moistened bread slices in bowl with enough stock to moisten.
Add all other ingredients with bread and enough chicken stock to make it real soft.

title: caribbean cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine all ingredients except lime slices. Serve over ice cubes; garnish with lime slices. Makes about 5 cups (4 servings).

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with the following:
Sausage, eggs, mushrooms, onions and green peppers. Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a casserole dish, add hamburger and mix with mushroom soup. Layer vegetables on top of meat.
Spread mashed potatoes over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all of the ingredients, breaking up potatoes. Mixture will be real thick.	Pour into 9 by 13 inch baking dish, bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill four loaf pans, 1/2 full only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until pasta is soft.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Serve immediately. Great after a cold day skiing!

title: real german potato salad
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until tender. Drain, peel and thinly slice or cut into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, salt and pepper to taste, vinegar, onions, bacon, eggs and salad oil.
Mix well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dairyman's delight pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with whipping cream.
Bake in large Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Don't overbake.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk well.
Add lemon juice and flavoring, beat well.
Pour into pie shell and chill 4 hours or more.
Top with favorite topping and enjoy.

title: danish kringle
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix dry ingredients with lard as for pie crust.
Mix beaten egg yolks and yeast into cooled milk, then mix with dry ingredients until smooth.
Cover and set in cool place overnight.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Roll very thin into 8 x 12-inch pieces.
Spread dough with slightly beaten egg white, then spread with fruit or custard filling.
Fold the dough, one edge over 2/3 and the other edge over entire surface making 3 layers.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Shape into a kringle or in strips.
Cover and let rise for 2 hours.
Brush dough with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Stir spaghetti mix and sauce together along with a tablespoon of sugar.
Brown hamburger meat.
Pour grease off.
Cook spaghetti; drain.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese and beat until blended.
Make meringue by beating egg whites until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Blend meringue into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Cool or chill 2 hours.
Serve plain or with sweetened whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: catfish creole style
directions: Rub the fillets well with salt and pepper.
In a large black iron skillet, saute the onions, bell pepper and celery in butter until vegetables are wilted.
Add the tomatoes, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Cook over a medium fire for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the catfish fillets, cover and lower fire.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
To serve, remove the fish with a spatula to serving plates.
Garnish with lemon slices and minced parsley.
Serve the sauce with steamed rice on the side.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix, oil, salt and baking soda.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press evenly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is browned at edges.
Meanwhile, prepare pie filling recipe as directed on can.
Pour over hot baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool.
Garnish with dollops of whipped topping.

title: french fried potato salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring the 4 cups water to a rolling boil. Carefully drop frozen potatoes into water; remove from heat. Immediately cover and let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain potatoes at once. Spread on paper towel.
Cut up any large pieces.
Sprinkle salt on the potatoes; cool.
In a bowl, combine eggs, radishes, celery, green onion and snipped parsley. Add mayonnaise, vinegar and potatoes. Toss mixture gently. Chill.

title: maple baked beans
directions: Cover and soak beans overnight.
Drain and reserve water. Boil salt pork and simmer.

title: party slush
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 (1/2 gallon) milk cartons and freeze to slush consistency. In punch bowl, mix slush with 2 (1 liter) bottles of ginger ale. Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup of water for 15 minutes.
Chop into small pieces after cooked.
Combine remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and more shredded cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except oil and applesauce.
In large skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil over medium to low heat.
In hot oil, spoon about 3 tablespoons potato mixture per pancake into skillet and flatten slightly.
Cook pancakes, turning once while cooking, until golden brown on each side.
Add oil as needed to cover bottom of skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm with applesauce.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over deboned chicken breasts. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with noodles and rice.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground meat. Add jar of picante sauce and chicken soup. Layer dish with tortilla chips.
Top with meat.
Alternate the two. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese is melted.

title: spiced lime fruit salad
directions: Peel, core and dice pineapple. Blend together lime juice, oil, lime peel and seasonings.
Mix the diced pineapple into dressing. Cut oranges into sections.
Halve the grapes. Use a melon baller and scoop out the cantaloupe.
Mix the remaining fruit in with the pineapple.
Marinate 30 minutes.
Place romaine lettuce leaves on plates. Divide the salad equal over the lettuce.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil in a 6-quart pot.
Add all other ingredients except tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 10 more minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato cheese pinwheels(makes 40 rolls)
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine juice, water and margarine.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat high speed 2 minutes.
Stir enough flour to make soft dough.
Cover bowl with foil.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours. When ready to shape, combine cheese and chives.
Punch dough down. Turn onto light floured board.
Divide in half.
Roll each 1/2 into 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Cut each rectangle into 20 (3-inch) squares.
Place on greased sheets 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon cheese mix on each.
Bring each point to center.
Cover. Rise until double, 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: orange egg nog punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add ginger ale when served.

title: double delicious bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chips and press firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter popsicles
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into Dixie cups. Insert stick.
Kids love them.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound flour well into the beef until steak is about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Add beef strips to the butter heated in a heavy skillet and brown on all sides, turning frequently.
Remove to bowl and cover to keep hot.
Add onions and cleaned, sliced mushrooms to skillet.
Cover and cook slowly, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return meat to skillet; stir in Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Cover and reheat to boiling. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve at once with hot fluffy boiled white or wild rice.
Serves 5.

title: instant fluffy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix and beat until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip or Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add to pudding.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.

title: hot buttered drink mix
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and spices.
Beat until smooth at high speed of electric mixer.
Stir in vanilla.
Store in airtight container for 1 month in refrigerator or 3 months in freezer.
Yields 4 1/2 cup mixture.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and make small meatballs (approximately 90).
In skillet combine 1 can jellied cranberry sauce, 1 bottle chili sauce, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Cut squash in half.
Remove seeds.
Cook onion and ground beef; brown.
Drain grease.
Add tomato paste and can of water; salt and pepper to taste.
Add mixture to squash.
Bake in 350° oven covered until squash is tender, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a large bowl.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add 1/3 cup salt and mix with crushed ice (enough to mix well with and cover with).
Let set for 3 hours and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring liquid mixture and cucumber mixture to boil.
Place in sterile jars and seal.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir together flour and baking powder.
Stir in creamed mixture. Divide dough in half.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar, oleo and shortening. Add egg yolks, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 1 cup of buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts.
Beat 5 egg whites stiff and fold into cake.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 3 layer pans.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then other ingredients. Use some of the flour to coat fruit.
Add fruit last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Make a stiff dough that is hard to roll out.
Flour dough heavy.
Roll out thin.
Flour bottom and top.
Roll; cut.
Leave lid off of noodles when cooking.

title: ring soup
directions: Add two ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and add 1 cup of rings.
Let simmer until rings are done.

title: freezer corn
directions: Place all the ingredients in pan and bring to a boil; stir often.
Boil 5 minutes.
Let cool and put in freezer bags.

title: chilled avocado soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except sour cream and lime slices.
Pour into soup bowls.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and slice of lime.
Serves 6.

title: millionaires(candy)
directions: Place caramels and milk in saucepan.
Melt over low heat.
Add pecans, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper. Chill.

title: 7-in one casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, place the following:
potatoes, ground beef, Minute rice, onions and peas, corn or green beans.
Add can of tomatoes, cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable chip dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese, mayonnaise, milk and the juice from the olives, then chop the onion, pepper, celery and olives finely. Mix them well into the creamed mixture.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches or two 9-inch pans.
Measure all ingredients together.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into pans.
Bake oblong pan 45 minutes, layers 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat sugar and cocoa together until it becomes real hot.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Boil 1 minute; add cream and pinch of salt.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Thoroughly brown pork chops on each side.
Mix water, bouillon and rice in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Place browned pork chops on top of rice.
Tightly cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla, then stir in the zucchini and drained crushed pineapple. Next, add the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, coconut and walnuts and blend. Pour into 2 greased and sugared bread pans or one 9 x 12 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done. Cool for 10 minutes and then turn out onto a rack to cool. If making cake, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting to finish.

title: sweet and simple pie
directions: Mix solid ingredients in a bowl.
Pour sweetened condensed milk in pie crust.
Pour dry ingredients into crust with milk and press down ingredients until milk rises up through them.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Sift cocoa, flour and salt together 3 times.
Cream together sugar, salad dressing and vanilla. Add flour mixture with sugar mixture alternately with water.
Bake in a 350° oven until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs by hand (no mixer at all!).
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and baking soda by hand.
Add cinnamon and flour; mix well.
Add apples and raisins, batter will be very thick.
Mix well and spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: polynesian dish
directions: Pour off juice from pineapple and put in with meat after meat has been browned.
Add a dash of arrowroot, ginger and soy sauce. Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mediterranean rice pilaf
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan on medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender.
Stir in broth and spices.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, apricots and raisins.
Return to boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut fresh fruit in large pieces.
Add a few broken nut meats. Mix pudding mix, milk, orange juice and sour cream.
Drip dressing over fruit.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Dump everything in order in pan. Cut oleo in patties and place over cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: picadillo(meat dish)
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add all remaining ingredients. Cook on low until potatoes are tender.
Instead of potatoes, you may substitute green beans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let
cream
cheese
come
to room temperature and cream with just
a little milk until nice and dippy (but not runny). Add all other ingredients to taste.
Let stand at least a few hours
or overnight
in refrigerator.
Remember garlic flavor will
develop stronger
taste
after it sets awhile.
A yummy party dip.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut and rinse good in a strainer.
Dissolve sugar and vinegar; add green onion, salt, green pepper, celery and pimentos.
Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture on top of crackers; add another layer of crackers.
Spread remaining mixture on top.
Put pie filling on top of mixture. Chill.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and pour into 24 foil cupcake liners. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for 5 minutes.

title: la. strawberry ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, salt and flour.
Add to scalded milk.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring often.
