Add small amount of hot milk to beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add egg mixture to hot milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Allow to cool.
Stir in evaporated milk and crushed strawberries.
Pour into freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: april's black satin cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding.
Add all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Beat 4 minutes.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Add a layer of chocolate chips and more nuts, if desired.
Pour rest of batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: real lemonade
directions: Combine all ingredients in these amounts to fill a pitcher. Stir.
Tastes much better than powdered!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and milk; blend well.
Add peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Add 6 tablespoons Cool Whip; stir well.
Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix enchilada sauce, soup, taco sauce, water and 1 teaspoon salt in saucepan and simmer about 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger meat, chili powder and garlic salt in skillet.
Heat tortillas one at a time in a small amount of grease or oil in skillet until soft and pliable.
Place one tablespoon of meat mixture, one tablespoon of grated cheese and one tablespoon of onion on each tortilla and roll.
Place in large baking dish.
Pour sauce over enchiladas and bake 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: salmon-corn chowder
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Saute onion and celery.
Stir in flour, add bouillon cubes, water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add salmon, stir in milk, corn, dill, salt and pepper.
Heat well, do not boil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: garlic bread pizza
directions: *You might need more or less depending on how thick you want the sauce.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and pepper in fat until onions are golden.
Add beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients and pour into greased 2 quart casserole, cover and bake about one hour in moderate oven (350°), removing cover last 15 minutes.

title: burger bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add salt, beans, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Heat until "bubbly."
Stir occasionally.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits in half and place, cut side down, around edge of casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all in large bowl (will be doughy).
Cover and let rise until double in size about 6 to 8 hours.
Turn onto floured board and knead out air bubbles.
Divide into 3 parts.
Grease 3 bread pans with Pam.
Let rise until to top of pan (around 3 to 5 hours). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef roast one dish meal
directions: Rinse roast. Coat with flour and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, lemon-pepper seasoning, salt and pepper. Slice onion and place on top. Surround with potatoes and carrots. Fill dish with water to 1/2-inch from top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° approximately 2 1/2 hours.

title: savory shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in soup, salt and thyme.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole dish. Place potatoes in mounds around edge of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add Doritos and dressing just before serving.

title: killer brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together; pour into pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Frost with chocolate buttercream frosting.
M-m-m good.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: With wet hands, shape into loaf in center of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick 4 medium potatoes and 1 onion. Peel and quarter lengthwise 4 medium carrots.
Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Cook one hour at 375°.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add stuffing and water. Mix well.
Pound steak, cut into 8 pieces.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing near center and roll.
Fasten with toothpick.
Brown in skillet. Add soup and water.
Cover.
Cook 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over.
Remove meat.
Add sour cream.
Heat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: irish stew
directions: Put meat, barley, onions and carrots in stew pot.
Cover with water and cook for 2 1/2 hours.
Peel and slice up potatoes, put into stew and cook for another 1/2 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Saute onions and potatoes until semi-soft.
Add corned beef and stir until separated.
Add water, a small amount at a time, to keep hash simmering and soupy but thick.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, melted butter, vanilla and coconut.
Place in a long baking dish.

title: walnut torte
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until thick and fluffy (about 10 minutes).
Combine vanilla, walnuts, bread crumbs, salt and nutmeg, then fold into egg yolk mixture.
In another bowl, beat the egg whites and remaining half cup of sugar until satiny.
Fold the egg yolk mixture into the egg white mixture.
Pour into a buttered and crumb lined spring-form pan (8-inch).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.
Remove to a rack to cool.
(It will shrink.)
When cool, remove rim from pan and cut torte crosswise into layers.

title: pickled onions
directions: Peel and slice onions paper thin.
Dissolve salt in water; soak onions 1 hour.
Remove to colander; wash well.
Add black peppers.
Put in quart jar; cover with vinegar.
Add garlic (if desired).
Seal.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion and drain.
Mix with soup and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and Tater Tots and bake 25 minutes more.

title: yogurt
directions: You will need 1 large Pyrex (or otherwise heatproof) mixing bowl.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order listed in a casserole dish. Heat in the microwave for 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: sizzling stir-fry chicken 'n peppers
directions: Place preserves in 1-quart Cook & Measure; stir cornstarch into soy sauce, then stir into preserves. Add sherry, garlic and pepper flakes. Microcook on High (100%) 3 minutes, stirring 2 times.

title: short bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Pat dough in pan that has 1/2 inch rim.
Prick dough with fork.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. While warm cut in thin strips or squares.
Extra good!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Dissolve jello, boiling water and either the cold water (or pineapple juice) and allow it to start to gel.
After jello thickens slightly, add all the ingredients.
Makes 2 nice 9-inch square dishes or 1 large glass container.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on the stove top until the mixture is thick.
Then pour into prepared pie shells.
Beat your egg whites until stiff.
Add a pinch of sugar and a teaspoon of vanilla.
Add to top of pies and brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine into a double boiler.
Simmer until thick.
Add meat, if desired.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Hand mix all ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves.
Put in freezer 1/2 hour.
Cut each half into 8 pieces and then freeze until ready to use.
When ready to serve, place uncovered in broiler, 1 or 2 minutes until golden brown.

title: vinegar and oil salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a small jar with a tight lid; shake until well mixed.
Makes enough dressing for 6 servings of a salad.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add the ziti and cook for about 5 minutes until tender being careful not to let the noodles overcook.
(They should not become mushy.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli until tender in small amount of water.
Place 1 layer of cooked rice in casserole, then mix water chestnuts with broccoli over rice.
Add mushroom soup to which milk has been added.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Rinse and drain. Slice mushrooms, zucchini and pepper.
Chop onion.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl with tight lid.
Make 2 packages of dry Zesty Italian dressing according to directions.
Pour over salad. Gently stir. Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: purple cow
directions: Place ice cream in a tall glass.
Pour grape juice over it and stir.
Fill glass to top with seltzer and gently stir again. Serve.

title: herman's sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large bowl.
Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Add potato.
Cover bowl with cheesecloth.
Let stand at room temperature 5 to 10 days until mixture has a fermented aroma. Stir 2 or 3 times a day.
To store, transfer starter to a jar. Cover with cheesecloth.
Refrigerate to use.
Bring desired amount to room temperature.
Replenish starter after each use by stirring 1/4 cup flour, 3/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature for at least 1 day, then refrigerate.
If starter isn't used within 10 days, stir in 1 teaspoon sugar or honey.
Repeat every 10 days unless replenished.

title: martha pafford's dry lima beans
directions: Wash dry lima beans.
Cook in a 2-quart boiler over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours, adding water as needed.
Add ham hock or ham bone along with salt and 4 tablespoons of bacon drippings and cook for 1 more hour, adding water as needed.
Beans should be tender and juice thick.
Serve with Salmon Patties and sliced onion.

title: nut cake
directions: Bake your favorite cake layers; I usually make six.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, mix thoroughly eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, then add apples and pecans.
Mix well by hand. Bake 1 hour in ungreased tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed hawaiian chicken
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish place chicken pieces. Cover.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Drain off excess.
Spoon sweet and sour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Chill for 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Using small teaspoon, make a roll of mixture long, shaping like a strawberry.
Roll in red sugar; dip top end in green sugar.
Leave on counter to dry out; store in closed container. Keeps good for weeks.
Yields about 80.

title: mock whipped cream frosting and filling
directions: Boil milk and flour together to make a paste; cool.
Combine sugar and Crisco and beat at high speed for 4 to 6 minutes.
Add cooled paste mixture and mix another 4 minutes.
Be sure to stir the flour and milk or it will be lumpy.
This can be used to fill cream puffs, too!!

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Boil together 20 minutes and put in small jars.
May use yellow tomatoes and lemon jello.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Soak wedge sliced cucumbers in water.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt to water.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, drain slices.
Mix onion, green pepper, sugar, vinegar and pickling spice together.
Put slices of cucumber in canning jars and pour mixture over cucumbers in each jar until covered.
Cap each jar. Let season in refrigerator for 2 weeks before eating.
Keep stored in the refrigerator.

title: marilyn's baked mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat 3 tablespoons of butter in large skillet.
Place washed mushroom caps (stems removed and set aside) in skillet, caps down, and saute 3 minutes.
Remove and arrange in buttered baking dish, rounded sides down.
Heat rest of butter in skillet; saute onions, green pepper and finely chopped mushroom stems about 5 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes. Fill mushroom caps, piling high in the center.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: marla's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix just until blended.
Bake one and a half hours in a 325° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all together.
Good with raw cauliflower, carrots, celery or broccoli.

title: quick taco pie
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spoon into greased 8-inch square dish.
Set aside.
Beat biscuit mix, milk and eggs with wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth, about 1 minute. Pour over meat.
Bake at 400°
for 25 to 30 minutes, or until center is set.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 2 minutes more until cheese is melted.
Cool for 5 minutes; garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, olives and, if desired, sour cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat sugar, margarine and milk.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; stir into sugar mixture. Add nuts. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: chopstick tuna or chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and water; add 1/2 can noodles.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: monterey bread
directions: * Can use Swiss, Romano or both.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Combine brown sugar, 1/3 cup flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: successful meringue
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in the small amount of cold water. Stir in the boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool. Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and then sugar gradually.
Beat in the cooled cornstarch and beat until of the right consistency to stand in pretty peaks.
Brown in 375° oven.

title: california succotash
directions: Wash and slice zucchini, saute in hot oil in large skillet until tender but not browned.
Add red bell pepper and onion to zucchini.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, slice corn off cob by cutting close to the cobs with sharp knife.
Add corn to zucchini mixture and heat thoroughly.
Cut tomato in halves crosswise and squeeze out the seeds and excess liquid.
Cut into chunks and add to vegetables along with salt to taste.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt chole's goulash
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onions and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain.
Add beans.
Add noodles, tomato sauce and cheese.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
If dry, add catsup.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Spray Pam, or grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add self-rising flour and mix well with fork until smooth.
Refrigerate for about 10 minutes for easy handling. Roll or pat out dough 1/2-inch thick and cut with a small pastry or biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Biscuits will not rise very much, but are very light and delicious.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: nicoise butter
directions: Beat all ingredients in a small bowl until well blended. Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together; cook until thick.
Cool and fill prebaked pie shell.
(Beat egg whites a little bit before cooking.)

title: salad rice and polish sausage bake
directions: Cook rice with water, onion and butter.
Brown sausage, that has
been cut into 1-inch diagonal chunks.	Blend sausage into a mixture
of
the celery, mustard, salad dressing, salt and	milk. Fold
all
ingredients
into
rice.
Garnish
with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated though.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large saucepan and cook on medium until it comes to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon off on wax paper and allow to cool.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add to chicken mixture, tossing to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with cantaloupe, grapes, and strawberries.

title: polly's spinach and rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach in boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly. Cook rice in 1 c. water with bouillon cubes.
Mix spinach, rice, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased casserole dish 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut in pieces. Boil spaghetti in broth of chicken.
Reserve 3/4 cup broth.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Place in a large bowl and mix together.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes. (Mix can be frozen and cooked in 30 minutes.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into lightly oiled casserole dish.

title: "the cake that never lasts"
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add pineapple and juice, pecans, eggs, oil and bananas.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: wassail
directions: Mix and heat 10 minutes.
Can float orange and lemon slices on top.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dodge county persimmon pudding
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients together and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes in covered casserole.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut in 1 cup Crisco and add 2 cups buttermilk; then add yeast. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 50 biscuits.

title: creamy fettuccine primavera
directions: Prepare fettuccine noodles as directed on package.
Steam the broccoli, carrots, onions and peppers.
Stir milk, cream cheese, and seasonings in a medium saucepan over low heat until smooth. Stir in chicken and Parmesan cheese.
Toss pasta and vegetables with sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs; beat smooth.
Add rhubarb and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell. Top with another pastry shell.
Cut slits in top.
Bake in hot oven (450°) 10 minutes, then in moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs.
Add milk and oil. Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple tart(serves 8)
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Put the flour, cubed butter and 2 teaspoons of the sugar in a food processor.
Start to blend and add the water.
When the dough forms a ball, transfer it to a floured board and roll it immediately into a circle of about 13 inches. Press it into a circular 12-inch shallow pie pan.
Sprinkle the dough with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Place the apple slices on the dough in a circular, overlapping pattern.
The pattern should be very precise, with only a slight overlap.
First, make the outer ring.
Then make an inner ring; the center will tend to rise to a peak, but this will flatten while baking.
If there is a hole remaining in the middle, fill it with some chopped apple.
Sprinkle the apple with the remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake the tart for 20 minutes.
Place the tart under the broiler for 1 minute to help caramelize the top.
The rims of the apple slices should be well browned.
Remove the tart from the broiler and brush the top with the 1 teaspoon of butter.
Serve hot.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Brush chicken with skim milk.
Coat with cereal mixture and place in nonstick baking pan.
Dot cutlet with reduced-calorie margarine and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: rocky road cups
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Stir peanuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows into pudding mixture.
Spoon into 8 dessert dishes or cups.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix
sugar,
salt and oil.
Add vinegar and shake well. Add celery seed and garlic; chill.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together and cook for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over cut up cabbage.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter. Pare and core apples (I prefer to also cut them up).
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Roll 1/8-inch thick. Cut in circles large enough to hold a small apple.
Place apple on circle.
Fill cavity with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bring dough up over apples, pressing edges together.
Place dumplings in pan with joined edges underneath in a greased baking pan.
Allow space between each.
Pour syrup over them.
Bake at 375° until tender, about 35 minutes.

title: kahlua dessert
directions: Bake cake according to the package directions. Cool. Mix pudding according to package directions. Break the cooled cake into bite size pieces.

In a large trifle or punch bowl, layer the cake pieces, Cool Whip, Heath bar bits, pudding and Kahlua until the bowl is full. Sprinkle the top with the shredded Nestle candy bar. Makes about 30 servings.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in bean pot or casserole dish. Garnish with bacon and bake at 350° until bacon is cooked, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, seasonings and sugar.
Add mushrooms and marinate 1 hour.
Stir in scallions and pimiento.
Serve in nest of shredded lettuce.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix like biscuit dough. Turn out on floured surface.
Roll thin (about 1/8-inch).
Cut in triangles or squares.
Drop into hot deep fat (365°).
Cook until brown. Serve with melted butter and honey.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour mixture into pan and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Blend eggs, butter, both sugars, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth; add oats, soda and M&M's or chips.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat all this up in bowl.
Batter will be thick.
Put in pan and bake in oven at 350° until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and let stand overnight in cold water.
Pack in jars.
Mix salt, water and apple cider vinegar.
Bring to boil. Pour vinegar in jars.
Place a grape leaf in the top of each jar. Seal.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat a frying pan and add the butter; put apples and raisins in pan and saute for a few minutes over medium heat until they are tender.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and spices.
Stir and set aside.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and both sugars in a large mixing bowl. Add each egg, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add sifted ingredients, milk and vanilla to batter.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Set ground chuck and taco seasoning aside. Combine soup, tomatoes and sour cream. Set aside. Take 1/2 bag of tortilla chips, gently crush chips into the bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. Pour beef mixture on top of chips. Top with the sour cream mixture and top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Cover with foil and cook
for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sour cream, then sifted dry ingredients, mixing after each.
Add flavoring; beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in large tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Take out of pan and allow to cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix beef and rice with tomato soup.
Put into casserole.
Season to taste.

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Bring margarine, syrup and sugar to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add corn flakes and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: vegetable mold
directions: Dissolve jello as directed.
Stir in Knox gelatine and salt. Stir in veggies, alternating, and mix well.
Let set.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cut butter into sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Stir in apples.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble bread slices, set aside. Brown sausage and drain. In a 3-quart casserole dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese, repeat. Pour milk into eggs. Add salt, pepper and mustard, mix well. Pour liquid over layers. Cover for 12 hours in refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, pudding mix, salt and cinnamon to a 3-quart casserole dish.
Stir in milk.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, at 325° for 3 hours. Mash with a fork when done to shred meat.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Beat well. Add bananas and fold in sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Put everything in a roaster with a cover.
Mix well.
Cook for 3 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: easy beef stew pot pie
directions: Pour beef stew into one of the pie crusts.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cover with the other pie crust.
Bake for 20-30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken continental rice
directions: Combine soup, onion and seasoning in saucepan.
Gradually add water and blend thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour soup mixture over uncooked Minute rice in shallow casserole dish.
Stir just to moisten.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes (or until rice absorbs most of the liquid).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings. Serve with fried chicken.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and baking powder into crumbs with hands.
Save some of this mixture (about 1/2 cup) to sprinkle on the top.
Break eggs into balance of crumbs and add milk.
Flavor with vanilla and beat very hard.
Pour into shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cinnamon and nuts may be sprinkled on the top if desired.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt oleo and mix 1/4 cup sugar, flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Cool.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour and eggs alternating but beginning and ending with flour. Beat well.
Fold in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan. On wax paper, combine next 6 items. Dip chicken in butter and roll in crumb mixture. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Add wine, onion and parsley to remaining butter.
Pour over and around chicken.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Preheat the oven to 500°. Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow dish. Stir well. Dip fish in eggs and dredge in crumb mixture. Place fish on a baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 500° for 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Core and seed peppers. Cut in 1 1/2 inch pieces. Place in large bowl. Cut onions in thin wedges; add to bowl. Quarter potatoes; add to bowl. Peel casing from kielbasa if necessary. Cut into 1/2 inch slices and add to bowl. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss with oil. Transfer mixture to shallow 1/2-quart baking dish or small roaster. Cover with lid or aluminum foil. Bake for 45 minutes. Remove and place cream into casserole. Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Boil all together until thick, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked chicken that makes its own gravy
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Arrange in single layer with skins down in melted butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered in moderately hot oven, 425°, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken
and bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes longer. Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onions and mushrooms to chicken.
Combine milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Return to oven.
Continue baking 15 to 20 minutes.

title: summertime pizza
directions: Spread and bake dough on cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 375° and let cool.
Prepare first topping by mixing cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cooked dough.
Add raw vegetables and sprinkle on cheese.
Cut in squares.

title: crawfish jambalaya in rice cooker
directions: Mix and cook in rice cooker.
Stir once when cover starts rattling.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter. Pour over Crispix in a bowl with a lid.
Add powdered sugar.
Put on lid and shake.
Eat and enjoy!

title: fried corn
directions: Put butter in pan; melt.
Put in corn, onion and pepper; cook for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Mix sauce and ground beef.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Make filling.
Place a little sauce in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Alternate layers of lasagne, cheese filling, meat sauce and lasagne.
Allow ends to extend up sides of pan.
Fold extended ends back over top and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Wash, quarter and cook tomatoes.
Cook until soft.
Put through food mill or colander.
Add all other ingredients and cook until thick (can use pressure cooker following directions for cooking low acid vegetables).
Makes 7 quarts.

title: pinwheel hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread tortillas with soft cream cheese.
Cover with thin slices of meat and shredded cheese.
Add olives, pimentos and picante sauce.
Roll up.
Seal edges with more cream cheese if necessary.
Slice and serve.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with mild salted crackers (like Ritz).

title: snack subs
directions: Open the hot dog buns and add the meat toppings and any other toppings.

title: touchdown casserole
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Stir to crumble.
Pour off fat. Stir in franks, celery, beans and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil. Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Using 2 2/3 cups potato flakes, prepare 8 serving recipe for mashed potatoes on package. Spread this over meat mixture.
Melt butter; stir in remaining 1/2 cup flakes.
Sprinkle over potatoes in dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned. Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti with spaghetti sauce; add poppy seed, cucumber dip and picante sauce.
Chill.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Combine cooked black-eyed peas, hot sauce, tomato sauce, mustard, pepper and salt. Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place onion slices, catsup and sausage on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until sausage is brown.

title: mrs. gladys howard's old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add first three eggs, one at a time, then
add 1 cup of flour.
Repeat.	Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican taquitos
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet.
Drain fat.
Set aside.
Warm tortillas in microwave, wrap in tea towel.
Put one teaspoonful of beef into tortilla, roll and secure with toothpick.
Make up enough to fry in skillet of hot oil.
When lightly browned, drain on paper towels.
Make as many as you like!
Place on cookie sheet, closely. Remove toothpicks.
Spoon picante sauce over each taquito, then sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot or cold.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter; add meat.
When meat is no longer pink, add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Simmer about 30 minutes. Grease a pan and layer tortillas and meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, evaporated milk, grated onion, parsley and horseradish in small bowl.
Spread over ham.
Roll each slice.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for several hours or until firm.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop all 3 ingredients and mix together.

title: mom's golden potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine rest of ingredients (except margarine) to make cheese mixture.
Place cheese mixture in a plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in bag to coat potatoes well.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in a layer in the pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, turning once after a half hour.
When golden brown, potatoes may be sprinkled with parsley.

title: chocolate chip cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the cookies, and blend together. Take one roll of cookies, sliced thin, and press into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan so the bottom is smooth.
Put cream cheese mixture on top of cookies so that it covers all the cookies.
Slice second roll and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool and then slice.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch shell (not deep dish).
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Bake a yellow cake from a mix. Glaze.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 8 ingredients together and add to the wet mixture.
Roll into balls.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
In pot, add kidney beans, chili beans, tomato soup, water, chili sauce, anise seed and meat mixture.
Cook on stove 2 hours and serve.

title: pineapple pistachio pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients; beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes and remove.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add warm milk and water; beat on low for 30 seconds, scraping bowl often.
Beat on high for 3 minutes, then stir in remaining flour.
Dough will be stiff.
Do not knead.
Grease 2 bread pans and coat with cornmeal.
Spoon batter into pans. Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise to double in size in a warm place.
Bake in 375° preheated oven until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately.
Cool.
Slice for toasting.

title: irish stew
directions: Boil stew meat until nearly done (about 1 hour).
Then, add diced
potatoes,
onions
and
seasonings.	Mix cornstarch with cold water until a	smooth paste is formed and add to the pot. When the potatoes
are done, add the tomatoes and simmer another 20 minutes.
This
recipe
takes
approximately
1 1/2 hours to cook and serves 4 people.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add taco seasoning mix.
Drain and set aside.
In large bowl, use lettuce, chopped onion and tomatoes to make a salad.
In large, deep pan, layer tortillas, salad, meat and soup until all is used (usually 3 to 4 layers).
Garnish with slices of green pepper.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: andy's dutch beans
directions: Cook bacon until not quite done; drain and set aside.
(Bacon should not be brittle.)
Saute onions in 2 or 3 tablespoons bacon fat.
Take 1 can of beans and wash; use other can as is.
Pour the unstrained can into large frying pan.
Add brown sugar; stir until sugar is melted.
Add onions and rest of the beans.
Flake bacon; add to mixture, along with catsup, spices and salt.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fold in lemon pudding.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 375° until cake springs back.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork chops on top of stove (save juice from chops).
Put chops in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put sauerkraut over top of pork chops.
Mix juice from sauerkraut and pork chops; add to the top of the sauerkraut dish.
Slice 2 apples and place on top of sauerkraut.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham glaze
directions: Cook ingredients and pour over ham during the last 15 to 20 minutes of baking.

title: taco quickie
directions: Saute beef, onion, pepper and taco seasoning.
Spread in a 9 inch greased pie plate.
Mix baking mix, eggs, and milk.
Sprinkle cheese on top of beef and pour mixture over the cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter with oil in large kettle. Add onions. Stir and cook, uncovered, over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sugar and salt and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle on flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to brown. In another pan, bring stock to simmer, then pour it over the onions. Add herbs and white wine. Simmer on low heat, partially covered, another 20 to 30 minutes. Add salt and pepper if needed.

title: tin roof pie
directions: Stir together peanut butter and corn syrup.
Add cornflakes and stir until coated.
Press in cake pan or pie pan.
Chill.
Put ice cream in crust and freeze.
Remove 10 minutes before serving.
Top with chocolate syrup and salted peanuts.

title: come on over cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Crush crackers.
Mix nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold crackers, nuts and baking powder mixture into egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes; cool completely.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Fold
together gently in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: sharon's watermelon fire and ice salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 3 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and 1 cup bananas.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add pecans and add to mixture.
Dissolve soda in water and add to mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: berry blizzard
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and whirl until smooth.
Serve cold in frothy glasses.
Number of servings:

title: cream of coconut
directions: Prepare cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, put holes in cake, then pour cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cool.
Next, layer crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and coconut.
Top with crushed pecans and cherries.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple bread pudding(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with pudding mix and cinnamon until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
In separate bowl, combine milk, pineapple with juice, raisins and vanilla.
By hand, blend milk mix to creamed mix (will look curdled).
Fold in bread.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Place in pan of water; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(An 8 x 8-inch pan, bake 1 hour.)

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Stir milk into lemonade.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.
(Can be frozen.)

title: spiced shrimp pape'
directions: Combine spices and mix with shrimp.
Add several bay leaves. Steam over vinegar and water or beer.
(Steaming only takes a couple of minutes.)
Do not overcook.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix dry Italian dressing with Zesty dressing; set aside.
Cook tri pasta; cut all other ingredients.
Mix all together.
Let it all set overnight.

title: fuzzy chucks
directions: Mix the first 3
ingredients.
(Can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Cover and	refrigerate.) Add champagne to orange juice mixture. Fill tall
glasses	with
ice.
Pour
mixture
over. Makes 10 cups.

title: avocado appetizer or dip
directions: Split an avocado.
Chop up and mix together with hard-boiled eggs and onion that you have browned.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Serve on crackers or as dip.

title: south carolina special cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add dry ingredients and flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mom's swiss steak
directions: Pound steak. Brown; salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients. Cook 1 1/2 hours in ordinary cooker. Cook 1/2 hour in pressure cooker.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill. Serve with crisp lettuce. Makes 2 cups.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Season pork chops; cut into chunks. Cut raw potatoes into chunks. Add potatoes and pork chops into individual packs of aluminum foil. Add hot sauce and butter. Bake at 400° approximately 45 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasonings and mix; set aside.
Heat refried beans and set aside in a baking dish. Add a layer of beans, ground meat and then a layer of cheese.
Add another layer of beans, meat and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Add tomatoes, onions and olives (chopped up) as a topping and sour cream, if you like or eat it as is.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Add drained pineapple, thawed strawberries, bananas and walnuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture in mold. Place in refrigerator until set. Spread with sour cream. Put balance of mixture on top.
Let set. Serves 18.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine sugar, oats, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Add margarine, then syrup and blend well.
Add vanilla. Sprinkle bottom of unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans and bake at 325° until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eastern shore baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch square pan (greased). Bake at 350° until firm.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Crumble and brown hamburger with onion.
In greased casserole dish, layer half hamburger, peas and rest of hamburger.
Pour on tomato soup; top with mashed potatoes.
Dot top with margarine; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake in small pieces and put into large oblong dish.
Mix first 4 ingredients and pour over cake.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast with warm water and set aside.
Put sugar, salt, oil and honey in a bowl.
Add scalded milk and mix.
Let this cool to room temperature and then add yeast and water and mix again.
Add 5 cups whole wheat flour, then one at a time, until all is used.

title: mom's seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add 7-Up.
When cool, add pineapple and bananas.
Put in refrigerator and chill until almost set.
Place marshmallows over top of salad and put back in refrigerator.
Add topping.

title: karen cronen's cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, crumble additional crackers on top and bake until crisp.

title: italian broccoli casserole(from:  southern living magazine)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Combine eggs, soup and oregano; mix well.
Stir in tomatoes and broccoli.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine peas and water in large kettle.
Bring to a boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Add ham bone, salt, pepper, marjoram and onions.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery, ham from bone and potatoes.
Continue simmering until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add more salt, if needed.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: angel roll
directions: Prepare cake mix as directions on box.
Spread evenly on ungreased large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Loosen sides and turn onto a clean dish towel.
Start at one end and roll cake up in the towel.
Cool completely in towel.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well on paper towel.
Combine butter, syrup, salt and powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Shape about 1 teaspoon sugar mixture around cherry, covering completely.
Put on wax paper and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: cranberry cordial
directions: Put all the ingredients in a jar in a dark closet for at least two weeks (the longer the better). Strain to serve. Save the cranberries to make your best ever cranberry nut bread.

title: country chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon oil in skillet 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in undrained tomatoes, broth and 1/2 cup water; bring to boil. Stir in corn, peas and rice; cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Boil chicken, cool and cube.
Save some broth.
Add cream of chicken and celery soups and onion.
Bring to a boil in crock-pot. Cook stuffing, using box directions, but use only 1 1/2 cups of water.
Mix with chicken mixture.
Add some broth, if desired. Serve on bread buns.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Mix last remaining ingredients, except for chocolate chips and nuts.
Place into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together chocolate chips and nuts; sprinkle on top of cake.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Add egg and oil.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Pour into 2 1/2-inch lightly greased muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: crock-pot pinto beans
directions: Place all in crock-pot and cover beans with water.
Cook all day until beans are soft.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: apple cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface to an 8 x 15-inch rectangle.
Spread apple filling and sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up tightly, jelly roll fashion, to make a 15 inch roll.
Pinch to seal the ends and seam.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch rolls using very sharp serrated knife or cut by wrapping thread around the roll, cross the ends of the thread and pull until cut.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let dough rise until double.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in oven preheated to 350° or until golden brown. Invert on plate and cool on a rack.
Drizzle glaze made from confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Pour back in marshmallow jar.
Strawberries are real good served with this dip.
Put a little on a plate and dip fruit into it.
Served with all kinds of cut up fruit.

title: dean and andrew's peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread.
Spread jelly on the other slice of bread.
Put slices together (with peanut butter touching jelly).
Cut diagonally into halves.
Serve on a plate.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Place peppers in 2-quart glass baking dish.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients except water in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon meat mixture into green pepper halves.
Pour water in bottom of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast for 22 to 24 minutes or until done (Medium to Medium-high).
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: large pineapple orange salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges and cottage cheese; add dry Jell-O. Stir in Cool Whip.
Sets up fast and is very tasty.
Can be halved to make smaller salad.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with oil or butter.
Pour the uncooked rice on bottom of pan.
Place chicken over rice.
You may season the chicken with salt and pepper before placing on rice. In a saucepan, combine the cream of chicken soup with 1 1/2 cans of water.
Cook until smooth.
Pour this over the chicken and rice.
Cover with chopped onion.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise into beaten eggs.
Stir in Ranch mix.
Add to cooked and drained zucchini.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Stir in crumbled saltines and sprinkle on grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots in salted water 20 minutes or until just tender; drain. Melt butter in saucepan and stir in preserves until blended.
Add nutmeg, salt, orange peel and juice.	Toss carrots with fruit mixture until well coated. Garnish with parsley. Serve at once.

title: emergency steak
directions: Mix all together.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Pat into shape of a T-bone steak (1-inch thick).
Broil.
Serve immediately.
Amount: 6 servings.

title: strawberry filled angel cake
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch horizontal slice from top of cake.
Then carefully hollow out remainder of cake, leaving 1/2-inch shell on bottom and sides including around the hole.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water if using fresh strawberries or juice from thawed berries (if using frozen).
If not enough juice, add water to make 2/3 cup.
Add berries and chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed after gelatin is slightly thickened.
Blend 2 cups of Dream Whip or Cool Whip with the gelatin mixture.
Spoon part of the gelatin mixture into the hollow cake.

title: orange sherbet  salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add sherbet, cream cheese, marshmallows and oranges.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate chip marble bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and blend.
Add vanilla and water.
Mix with flour, salt and soda (which have been sifted together).
Stir in nuts.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and put into a 375° oven for 2 minutes, then remove and run a knife through the batter, making a marbled effect.
Return to oven and cook 10 minutes.
Let cool slightly; cut into squares.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: crepes-mandarin dessert
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, beginning with liquids. Blend at high speed for 20 to 30 seconds.
Scrape down sides of the container.
Blend a few more seconds.
Crepe batter made in a blender can be used immediately or refrigerated until needed.
If mixture thickens on standing, thin to the right consistency with a little milk.
Crepe batter should be thin enough to run freely around the bottom of the crepe pan when it is tilted.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, shortening and margarine in a mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs.
Beat for 1 minute. Add the flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in the pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 minutes. Cool on the cookie sheet for several minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 72 servings.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Sift flour, measure, add salt.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add melted butter.
Beat slightly (may appear lumpy).
Pour into well-greased custard cups.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 popovers.

title: tabbuli salad
directions: Soak wheat in cold water for at least 1/2 hour. Squeeze dry by pressing between palms of hands.
Chop onions, parsley, mint leaves and tomatoes very fine.
Add wheat, lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper. Mix well. Serve with fresh lettuce leaves, grape leaves or steamed cabbage leaves.
The leaves are to be used like scoops. Serves 6.

title: dark devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Dissolve cocoa in boiling water. Add baking soda to hot coffee.
Combine flour and baking powder. Add all ingredients to creamed mixture.
After adding flour, beat only until flour disappears (mixture will be thin).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Spread prepared mustard on pork chops, then flour. Brown chops and cook thoroughly. Pour soup and water and let simmer. Serve with mashed potatoes. Mmm good!!

title: christmas creatures(not edible)
directions: Mix together the flour and salt; make hole and pour in 1 cup of coffee.
Mix together.
Add additional coffee if necessary. Form into balls and store in plastic bags.
Roll out to 1/4 inch. Cut and decorate.
Punch ornament holes.
(Can use cookie cutters.)
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 1/2 hours on cookie sheets. Ornaments can be painted and/or shellacked, if desired.

title: new england apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together margarine and both sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
In medium bowl, combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; stir to combine thoroughly.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Spoon into greased 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out almost clean. (Because of the apples, the toothpick will be moist.)
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes; turn out onto serving dish.
When completely cooled, dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 16.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: p.d.q. pickles
directions: In glass or crockery bowl, alternately layer cucumbers and onions.
In pan, combine all other ingredients.
Bring to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Cool slightly.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Store up to 1 month in refrigerator. Makes 7 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables.
Should use Hellmann's mayonnaise or taste will not be the same.

title: shrimp and linguine
directions: Shell shrimp.
Boil shells in water to cover for 30 minutes. In frying pan, saute butter, oil, garlic and parsley; allow to cool.
Discard shells.
Add water to frying pan.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Clean and cut shrimp in chunks, add to frying pan and simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Serve over linguine.

title: noodle pudding(jewish; luchun kugel)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for about 8 minutes.
Drain. While noodles are cooking, mix all other ingredients together. Then add to cooked noodles.
Put into very large Corning Ware (or 2 large baking dishes).
Cook, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased pan.
Let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cooked.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine butter and
cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat	eggs
on high for 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, butter, milk
and
vanilla.	Beat
well and spread over crumb crust.
Chill
for
minutes.
Add pineapple, bananas and frozen topping
to	top of filling.
Sprinkle with pecans, top with cherries.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.

title: southern style glazed carrots
directions: In large saucepan, cook carrots in boiling water to cover until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: diabetic banana raisin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients carefully.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nutmeats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: scallops with piquant tomato cream(the maine course)
directions: Cook angel hair pasta according to package directions and toss with butter to coat.
Saute scallops in butter until firm, but not tough.
Stir in heavy cream and salsa.
Simmer until warmed through; sprinkle in chopped parsley and pour over cooked pasta. Garnish with parsley sprigs and lemon wedges.
Delicious!

title: oriental salad
directions: Chill vegetables, rice and shrimp.
Combine and blend together the oil, vinegar, soy sauce, curry powder, salt, monosodium glutamate, celery seed and sugar; beat to blend well.
Pour dressing over chilled vegetable-rice-shrimp mixture.
Toss slightly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add next three ingredients.
Mix well.
Cool over low heat.
Add cheese last.
Cook until all cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: slow-roasted ribs
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Pour about 1 cup water into a roasting pan. Put the ribs, fat side up, on a rack in the roasting pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue roasting until the ribs are tender, about 2 1/2 hours longer.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Fill a large bowl about 3/4 full of flour.
Make a shallow well in flour; cut in shortening until it crumbles.
Add buttermilk and knead until it forms a ball.
Roll out onto floured surface until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased biscuit pan.
Bake in a hot oven, about 400°, until browned.
I just pinch the dough off and roll biscuits slightly in hand before putting them in pan instead of rolling out dough.

title: hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put remaining ingredients in layers in pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares before serving.

title: old world sauerkraut
directions: Fry bacon.
Add flour to bacon drippings.
Stir in sauerkraut. Mix.
Place sauerkraut mixture and bacon pieces in crock-pot.
Add all others.
Cook on low, 7 to 9 hours (high, 3 to 4 hours).

title: beef patties parmesan
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 4 patties and place in ungreased shallow pan.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garnish with green olives.
Serve with noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve on small breads or crackers.

title: seafood cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a rectangular pan and bake at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green gazpacho
directions: Puree fruit and vegetables in small batches in a food processor, adding white grape juice as necessary to keep the blade from clogging.
Do not puree completely; the gazpacho should be chunky.
Transfer the mixture to a bowl; add the remaining grape juice, lime juice, chopped mint, salt and white pepper to taste. Cover and chill at least 4 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 3 quarts water in a 2 gallon container.
Add the 3 sodas.
Makes 48 (7 ounce) cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and mix with next 5 ingredients.
Melt margarine and mix with herb dressing.
Spread on top of casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook onion in bacon grease until translucent.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and flour; stir.
Add vinegar.
Add 1/2 cup water. Bring to boil.
Add potatoes and celery seed.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef, egg and crumbs; shape into 16 meatballs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, brown meatballs.
Spoon off fat.
Add gravy.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: swedish salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Just before serving, add 1/2 pint whipped cream to the Dressing and fold into the salad.

title: spinach spread or salad(serves 15)
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all water.
Combine all ingredients except eggs.
If serving as salad use diced Cheddar cheese (1/2 inch cubes) and garnish top with sliced eggs.
If a cracker spread is desired, change Cheddar cheese to shredded variety and add a little more Miracle Whip for easier spreading. Eliminate eggs. Extra horseradish and Tabasco give it some real zip.
Also crumbled bacon as a garnish is an option.

title: mexican-style cabbage soup
directions: Heat oil
in
large Dutch oven.
Add cabbage and onion. Cook over
medium heat until slightly browned, stirring often. While cabbage
cooks,
remove
core
from tomatoes with tip of sharp paring
knife.
Quarter
2 tomatoes and place in blender jar
with garlic, tamari sauce and molasses.
Blend at medium speed	until smooth.
Add blended mixture to cabbage and bring to
a boil. Chop remaining tomato and add to soup.
Add chili powder
and cumin.
Stir
in
cup water more, if needed. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Steam asparagus for 2 to 3 minutes in a small amount of water. Combine bouillon cubes, ginger, soy sauce, sugar and water; heat until bouillon dissolves.
Serve garnished with radish slices.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually stir in lemon juice, lemon rind and water.
Cook until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: short cookies
directions: Mix together and roll very thin.
Cut cookies with cookie cutters and bake in a 350° oven about 8 minutes.

title: cappuccino chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, Espresso powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, stir together milk, butter, egg and vanilla until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add milk mixture and stir just to combine.
Stir in chips.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick tested in the center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from tin.
Serve warm or cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly. Serve with cracker or bagel crisps.

title: tijuana pork chops
directions: In skillet brown chops (use shortening, if necessary).
Pour off fat.
Add soup, chili and garlic salt.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add peas and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes more or until done. Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating between.
Add pumpkin and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Grease 3 loaf tins and fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Bread is dark brown and moist.

title: peanut butter rice krispies bars
directions: Put Rice Krispies in a large bowl.
On medium heat, melt sugar, Karo syrup and peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies and stir.
Spread mixture in buttered cookie sheet.
In small saucepan, melt butterscotch chips and milk chocolate chips and spread over Rice Krispies.

title: apple walnut muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Stir to mix.
Whisk milk, eggs, margarine to blend; pour over flour mixture.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Stir in grated apple.
Spoon batter into muffin tins, 2/3 full. Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and let both cheeses come to room temperature.
Mix ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll ball into paprika and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling point in saucepan.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add 7-Up; mix well.
Chill until partially set. Add pineapple; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill until set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
After mixing well, pour into greased 8 inch square pan and bake at 450 degrees for about 20-30 minutes or until brown.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Bring the butter, sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper; let cool and serve.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Break hard pretzels into small pieces (the smaller, the better) or use pretzel sticks.
Mix all ingredients except pretzels
in a cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Add broken pretzels and coat thoroughly.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over cereal; stir very good.
Dump sugar over and shake to coat.

title: heavenly rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add boiling water and allow to cool.
Add yeast.
Stir in beaten egg, salt and the shortening mixture.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough, stirring with a wooden spoon.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan.
Cover with bacon.
Pour over all tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding in sugar, still beating.
Fold in sifted flour and salt, coconut and vanilla. Drop on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring nectar to boil and stir in jello.
Cool.
Add one can crushed pineapple (save juice).
Soften cream cheese; add celery and nuts.
Add juice to spreading consistency.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Simmer bones in water until meat falls from them, about 3 hours.
Remove bones from liquid.
Cut up meat.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 (1-cup) servings, about 175 calories per serving.

title: milo's salad dressing
directions: Using a fork
in a wooden bowl, crush garlic with salt. Pour in olive
oil and mix well.
Combine other ingredients in order listed
(hot
sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lime or lemon juice, wine vinegar
and mustard), mixing well after each one. Prepare to use
with
green
tossed
salad or bean salad.
Let marinate at least 1 hour.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle grated onion and garlic powder over kraut; spread on sour cream.
Crumble beef over cream.
Spread cheese over beef.
Top with bread cubes.
Pour melted butter over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one is added. Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: pineapple mandarin cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, liquid from oranges, oil and eggs.
Mix in by hand mandarin oranges.
Bake in 2 layer round pans according to package directions.
Cool.
Slice each layer in half so you have 4 separate layers.
Combine Cool Whip and pineapple and frost all layers.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 easily.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a large mixing bowl. Stir well.
Pour half of mixture into a greased skillet; top with cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.
Bake in a 10 or 12-inch skillet.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixtures resemble coarse crumbs.
Add raisins and gradually stir in milk, mixing just until blended.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Mix brown sugar, butter and boiling water.
Pour over batter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.

title: frankfurter macaroni casserole
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy skillet of saucepan.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add soup. stirring, until blended.
Mix flour with a little of the milk to a smooth paste.
Add remaining milk, mixing thoroughly.
Add to soup mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add frankfurters and macaroni, stirring just until blended.

title: frozen party salad
directions: Gradually add salad dressing to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended. Stir in fruit, sugar and coloring.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Freeze.
Unmold on platter.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook ground chuck, bacon and onions together until meat loses its color and onions are tender. Add ketchup, mustard, vinegar, salt and brown sugar. Mix together well and put in Dutch oven or crock-pot. Add beans and cook for 30 minutes. Simmer longer for more flavor.

title: rich turkey gravy
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, stir flour into hot drippings.
Cook and stir until dark brown.
Stir in water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually with spices.
Cream until light. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Dredge fruit in 1/2 cup flour. Beat eggs until light. Add alternately with remaining flour, stirring until well blended. Stir in dredged fruit, nuts and applesauce.
Bake in greased pan in slow oven at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done, depending on size of pan.
I use bread pans.

title: butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add 24 ounce bag butterscotch chips and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Place balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Always put dough on cool cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen or more.

title: peanut butter squares(like reeses peanut butter cups)
directions: Mix everything together, except frosting.
Pat into a greased 13x9-inch pan.
Frost with chocolate frosting (microwave frosting just enough to soften to spread easier).

title: my company special grape gelatin mold(1940's)
directions: Soften gelatin in apple juice in saucepan.
Heat to dissolve. Add sugar and dissolve.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until slightly thickened (foaming will subside).
Stir in grapes, oranges and nuts.
Pour into mold or dish.
Chill until firm.
Put on lettuce lined plate.
Very good.

title: katie's chicken wings
directions: Wash and dry chicken wings; disjoint and discard wing tip ends.
Combine and mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Dip wings in combined melted butter and garlic salt and then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Increase temperature to 450° and bake 15 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Yield:
32 pieces.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil and dissolve jello.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thick.
Stir in cranberry sauce and nuts. Pour in 2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels (not too finely crushed), sugar, oleo and pecans. Press lightly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping.
Spread on top of first layer.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
When partially congealed, put on top of second layer.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet; let thicken. Add pineapple, Mandarin oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip; refrigerate.

title: lovetta's potatoes
directions: *Creamy chicken mushroom soup can be used in place of cream of chicken soup.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown noodles in butter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hot slaw
directions: In
mixing
bowl, sprinkle cabbage with salt. Let stand 1/2 hour at room temperature. Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel
and crumble.
Sprinkle over cabbage. In skillet, bring
to boil
vinegar,
water
sugar and pepper.
Pour over cabbage. Serve warm.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions in oleo until limp, not brown; add peeled shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes until pink.
Add all other ingredients, soups, rice, salt and pepper.
I prefer to mix all before adding salt and pepper.
Sometimes you find you do not want more.
Pour in large casserole and bake 1/2 hour or until crusty. This makes about 10 servings.
Will make 3 medium casseroles.

title: different ham slices
directions: Put center cut ham slices in pan.
Pour small can Hawaiian Punch and small can pineapple (slices or crushed) over ham. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Pour off juice.
Cut oven off and let set in oven for 2 to 3 hours, covered, before serving.
Tastes like country ham.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix well. Pinch off and roll into small balls. Turn over in oil in pan to coat top of biscuit with oil. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt margarine, Saute seasonings about 10 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Vegetables should still be crunchy.
Mix everything in large casserole.
Top with Italian bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour until hot and bubbly.

title: mum's lemon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, salt, rind, juice, yolk of eggs (well beaten) and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour in pudding dish.
Bake in slow oven until brown (about 350°).

title: icebox cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Store in refrigerator or put in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May store batter in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days and use cold.

title: low-fat condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add all other ingredients. Place in crock pot and let cook all night on low. Take off lid in the morning and beans will get a little thicker.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together the last 3 ingredients.
Add
to
the
first
5 and let stand for about 2 hours.

title: cooked beets
directions: Heat all ingredients and stir with fork.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and place in bottom of a greased baking dish.
Mix together butter, fruit, sugar and water; pour over dough mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Pour melted shortening over oatmeal.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix flour and salt; set aside.
Mix yeast, water and sugar; set aside.
Mix shortening, egg and milk.
Mix ingredients together; let set for 1 hour.
Roll out onto pan.
Let set another hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and cut in lard.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Add buttermilk.
Make well in dry mixture and pour liquids in.
Stir together.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Let rise, covered, for 3/4 hour until double.
Punch down dough and knead 1 minute.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on greased baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Cover and let rise 1/2 hour. Brush with melted butter and bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven at 425°.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add a couple of tablespoons of artichoke juice to desired consistency.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips (Fritos are best).

title: mary ann's turtles
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels and milk.
Stir in pecans and mix well. Drop by small teaspoons on buttered cookie sheet. Chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip caramel pieces in chocolate mixture.
Store covered.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: spoon bread
directions: Make mush of the meal and 2 cups of milk.

Add the rest of the milk, well beaten eggs, salt and baking powder and melted butter. Bake in a medium oven about 30 minutes or until set and brown. Serve with butter in same Pyrex or Earthenware dish in which it was baked.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth out the cherry pie filling, then pineapple on top of that.
Sprinkle sugar over and add dry cake mix.
Smooth this out to cover fruit.
Pour melted margarine over and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Gradually add enough of the milk to make a paste.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining milk. Cook slowly, stirring constantly to prevent sticking, or cook over hot water in top of double boiler.
When thickened, remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: haystacks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheet with foil, then line with a layer of crackers.
Combine butter and sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips over mixture and spread with a spoon or spatula.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Put in refrigerator.
After it hardens, break into pieces and store in airtight containers.

title: jan's favorite blueberry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and cream cheese.
Fold in whipped cream, berries and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pie crusts. Refrigerate!

title: mother's pastry
directions: Cut Crisco in flour and salt.
Break egg in mixing cup.
Add vinegar and water to make 1/2 cup.
Stir and add to dry ingredients.
Mix good.
Makes 2 big, deep shells or 3 small. Keeps in Ziplocs in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Use for serving salads - an edible bowl.

title: lime pie
directions: Stir together pineapple, lime juice, sweetened condensed milk and food coloring.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate. Just prior to serving, top with whipped cream.

title: california meat loaf
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
