Add next 9 ingredients and saute until onion is translucent, about 7 minutes. Transfer to large bowl.
Mix in all remaining ingredients except butter and pepper.
Spoon mixture into loaf pan, patting top to even.
Bake 1 hour.
Pour off accumulated juices on top and bake an additional 15 minutes until brown.
Meanwhile, melt butter in small heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add bell pepper and saute until tender.
Unmold meat loaf.
Sprinkle with bell pepper.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Sprinkle crushed peanut butter cups or chocolate chips on top of pie, if desired.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, soup, eggs, onion, lemon juice, seasonings and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Mix lightly.

title: pork jambalaya(good! good! good!)
directions: Cut up onions, celery, bell pepper and green onions.
Set aside.
If using fresh garlic, prepare now.
Season meat with salt, black and red pepper.
Do not use any oil.
Place pork in a cool Dutch oven and bring heat up slowly so meat won't stick.
Brown well and add small amount of water and after water is gone, add small amount more water and flour and 1/2 yellow onion and simmer down again, careful not to burn flour.
After water is gone, add 5 1/2 cups water and bring to boil, stirring to get all gremees from sides and bottom of pot.
Simmer while sauteing veggies and garlic and seasonings.
Add to meat with rice and bring to boil for 3 minutes, stirring for rice not to stick.
Turn low and cover cooking 25 minutes, then fire off.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.
Any meat or chicken can be used and also served stewed or Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.

title: elegant crab soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in flour, then the milk, salt and peppers.
Stir until well heated and thickened.
Add crabmeat and then cream.
Heat well.
Add the egg, pressing it through a sieve.
Add sherry and Old Bay seasoning and more salt and pepper if necessary.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 greased loaf pans (7 3/4 x 3 5/8-inch).
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Saute onions in shortening. Add remaining ingredients, except hot dogs. Cook for 10 minutes. Slice hot dogs into bite size pieces. Add to sauce. Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pork chop-rice casserole
directions: Place chops in bottom of flat 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of the onions, salt and pepper.
Spread rice over onions.
Add mushrooms with juice.
Cover with chopped tomatoes. Sprinkle with remaining onions, salt, pepper and the sugar.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lime jello per directions and let set up until firm in large flat casserole.
After set, dissolve lemon jello in water in pan over heat; add marshmallows and melt.
Add pineapple juice (1 cup) and cream cheese, beat until blended.
Stir in 1 cup drained pineapple and cool.
Then fold in mayonnaise and whipped cream. Pour over set lime jello and when this is set firm, prepare cherry jello per directions.
Pour over firm cream cheese layer.
Chill. It takes over one day to get this set good.

title: ham and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Place 8 slices of trimmed bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (Pammed). Layer ham and cheese.
Top with bread.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over and refrigerate overnight.
Pour melted oleo over bread. Top with crushed cereal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix the oatmeal and buttermilk together.
Beat in the remaining ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Bake and enjoy.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut into chunks.
Combine with drained mixed vegetables, chicken broth and chicken soup.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix flour, melted margarine and milk. Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Cook for 2 minutes at 300°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Stir until oats are coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Spread the uncooked rice over bottom of dish and lay chicken pieces on top.
Spoon soup evenly over chicken.
Pour water over soup, then sprinkle onion soup mix over water.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch twice baked potatoes
directions: Slice baked potatoes lengthwise. Scoop flesh of potatoes into a large bowl. Place the skins on a baking sheet. Add the butter to the potatoes and mix well. Add the Ranch flavor mix to potatoes and mix well. Spoon equal amounts of potato mix back into the skins and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in large saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cereal, stir gently until coated. Put powered sugar in a large paper bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake until cereal is coated. Spread in single layer on wax paper. Let set until dry.
Store in covered container.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar in small bowl.
Add flour, then nuts.
Reserve 3/4 to 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(If using a glass pan, reduce heat to 325°.)
Blend granulated sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Spread over baked crust; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (325° for glass pan).
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sausage cabbage noodle medley
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium high heat. Add onions, sausage and red pepper.
Saute 4-5 minutes or until tender crisp.
Stir in cabbage, sugar, dill, vinegar, salt and pepper until blended.
Cook 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Add egg noodles; toss to coat.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: baked beans in tomato cups
directions: Wash
tomatoes;
cut out stem end and scoop out center, leaving
thick wall.
Sprinkle inside of cups with celery salt and sugar
and fill with baked beans.
Butter a shallow baking pan and set
the
filled
tomatoes
in it.
Place 1 slices of bacon across
each
tomato
and
bake until bacon is crisp; at 350° for 20
minutes.
The
scooped out centers can be stewed and
seasoned with salt, prepared mustard and a little sugar. Strain and serve as a sauce around baked tomatoes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put Oreo cookies in freezer overnight.
Grate in blender (14 Oreos at a time).
Prepare pudding according to instructions on the box.
Add cream cheese to pudding mixture, then fold Cool Whip into cream cheese and pudding mix.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll up from short side.
Wrap and freeze.
Slice and put on top of Ritz cracker.

title: circus mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store mix in airtight container. Yields 7 cups.

title: zucchini pineapple bread or cake
directions: Cream together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla, then stir in the zucchini and drained, crushed pineapple.
Next add the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, coconut, walnuts and blend.
Pour into two greased and sugared bread pans or one 9 x 12 cake pan.

title: microwave chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together by hand or cherries will mush.
Put into microwave pan.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: todd's chicken delight
directions: Heat large skillet or wok on high.
Melt margarine.
Add onions, pepper, then mushrooms.
Saute to your liking.
Move veggies to the side and fry up the chicken.
Once cooked, mix with veggies.
Add Grey Poupon.
Mix. Add wine.
Mix. Add spices.
Mix. Let simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Heat oven on broil 350°.
Cover skillet with Mozzarella then top with tomatoes and parsley.
Put under broiler if using skillet, if using electric wok, just let the cheese melt in.
Let broil for 2 to 4 minutes.
Serve over noodles and a side of salad and applesauce.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of boiling water 5 to 7 minutes or until squash is tender; drain well.
Place vegetables in electric blender and process until smooth.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fruit compote
directions: To skin peach or apricots, dip into boiling water for 30 seconds, then plunge into cold water to stop the cooking process. Skins will then slip off.

title: witch's brew
directions: Put everything in a blender and whip.
It's good.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat, stirring until thick. Before serving, stir in vanilla and butter.
Blend well.

title: italian sausage stew
directions: Dice onion and cut up Italian sausage.
Brown together in olive oil.
Slice carrots, celery and mushrooms; quarter potatoes. Place in a 3-quart roasting pan.
Add onions and Italian sausage. Add Italian stewed tomatoes with juice, garlic, Italian seasoning and water.
Bake 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to box instructions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Put 1/2 cup in mixture and sprinkle 1/2 cup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix butter or margarine and sugar.
Add the 2 eggs and beat. Add milk, lemon rind, flour, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Put in 1 large or 2 small bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix juice of one lemon and 1/2 cup sugar.
When done poke holes in bread and pour lemon/sugar mixture over the top.

title: easy morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in fluted Bundt pan. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls. Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until mixture bubbles. Pour over rolls. Cover tightly with foil and let stand on countertop overnight or 8 hours. Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Invert carefully over serving dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover first 3 ingredients with ice; soak 3 hours.
Drain water off.
Do not rinse!
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Have cucumbers drained.
Put cucumbers in liquid and let get hot through and through.
Do not boil!
Put in jars and seal.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Stir in a large bowl with Cool Whip.
Pour in Jell-O.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Dice bacon; add onion and fry over medium heat until bacon is almost crisp and onions are clear.
Add frozen peas and rice, then water.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Cook 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts to chocolate mixture to coat nuts.
Combine the two mixtures.
Mix only until blended.
Do not beat.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Beat until fluffy and add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes and reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake an additional 45 - 50 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 wooden skewers.

title: dad emery's cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great seasoning for chicken, fish, crabs, shrimp and crawfish.

title: sunny angel cake
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, and salt until stiff. Slowly add sugar and flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour into angel cake pan.
Beat hot water, egg yolks, sugar, and salt for 3 minutes or until lemon yellow.
Add flour mixed with baking powder and beat well.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into pan on top of white mixture.
Bake in a very slow oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease two quart casserole.
Add salt and pepper to basic white sauce.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce, ending with sauce.
Bake covered 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking 30 minutes more until potatoes are tender and top is browned.

title: great tasting lasagna without the guilt
directions: Cut beef into very small pieces.
Brown beef and onion in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce, tomato paste and 3 1/2 cans of water.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cook noodles according to package directions; rinse and drain.
Mix together Parmesan cheese, egg substitute and cottage cheese.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, soften gelatin in cold water.
Add undrained crushed pineapple.
Cook and stir until mixture starts to boil.
Reduce heat; continue to cook for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Cool.

title: sweet violet bread
directions: Stir together the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine the egg, milk and oil.
Add the egg mixture to the flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Gently stir in the nuts and minced violets.
Pour batter into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
If desired, gently press 2 or 3 whole violet leaves into the batter in each pan.
Sprinkle sugar over batter in each pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on wire racks.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well. Add pineapple, carrots, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well; add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: baked onions
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole place, alternately, 1 layer of thinly sliced onion, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Pour soup and milk over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy rice
directions: Layer ingredients; heat in microwave.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Combine vegetables, sour cream, soup, 1/2 of cheese and onion rings and pepper and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place breasts in large pan and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley, celery and 1 stick of butter. Bring to a slow boil and let simmer until chicken is falling off bones.
Remove chicken.
Place in a bowl and refrigerate.

title: diabetic salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup water.
Mix all together and refrigerate.
May add nuts.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Beat together.
Layer into a big bowl, ending with the Oreo layer.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk. Add cool whip. Mix well. Layer pan with crackers. Pour pudding mix over crackers. Layer crackers again over pudding. Spread frosting over crackers. Refrigerate.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients except pie shells into saucepan.
Bring to boil and stir 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool 15 minutes.
Pour into pie shells; serve topped with whipped cream. Store in refrigerator or freezer.
May be eaten frozen.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes after taking from freezer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together well kneading in Bix-Mix and cheese.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Drain off grease and place on paper towels until ready to serve.

title: fluffy coconut pudding
directions: Soften
gelatin
in
cold
water.
Add boiling water and stir until
dissolved.
Cool
to
room
temperature.
Beat egg whites with
salt until frothy.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time and beat well after each addition.
Continue beating until mixture holds
a
peak
when beater is lifted..
Slowly beat in gelatin. Add
vanilla to whipped cream.
Mix and fold into egg whites. Fold in coconut.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.

title: brown sugar pecan pie
directions: Bake in unbaked 9-inch pie crust at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried fish fillets
directions: Beat egg and milk together until blended.
Dip fillets in milk mixture, then in mixture of flour and salt.
If heavier coating is desired, dip in milk and flour mixture again.
Fry in hot Crisco until golden brown.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: warm caramel pears
directions: Simmer pear juice, brown sugar, syrup and butter until smooth. Add pears and heat through.
Serve warm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix puddings and milk.
Combine these 2 mixtures and fold in Cool Whip with 1/2 cookie crumbs.
Layer crumbs, pudding and crumbs in plastic flowerpot.
Can add gummy worms in layers and top with artificial flowers.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, adding the lettuce last.
Stir or toss lightly.

title: california baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, in single layer in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion soup and bacon. Add water and sherry.
Cover.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: seven layer cookie bar
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter. Press mixture into lightly sprayed baking dish. Sprinkle each of the following ingredients by layers over the crust: chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts, coconut and then top with the condensed milk. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour into greased casserole dish (2-quart) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 10 minute pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into the cream cheese; add rest of milk and chocolate mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, salt, vanilla, nuts and flour; shape and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine rhubarb with 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, oil, eggs, sour milk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add the rhubarb and sugar mixture.
Stir well until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.
Combine the last 5 ingredients and cook 3 minutes. Pour topping over cake while still warm.
(3 tablespoons of vinegar to make sour cream)

title: wacky cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Cream cheese and margarine together. Gradually add flour, salt and pepper.
Put mixture through cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.
Cool well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Into large size mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and other hot milk.
Add bread and let stand until mixture is lukewarm.
Stir in the next five ingredients.
Turn into large casserole or baking dish.
Bake in 350° (moderate) oven until a sharp bladed knife inserted near center of pudding comes out clean, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cranberry nut casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar together.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine the oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, melted butter and nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over top of cranberry and apple mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After 45 minutes, check; if it seems dry, add a little water.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Slowly add milk.
Cook over medium-high heat until a very soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Slowly stir while cooking.
Remove from stove. Add vanilla, margarine and peanut butter to fudge.
Stir until fudge starts to thicken.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: sweet potatoes in orange cups
directions: Cut oranges into halves and extract juice and pulp.
Scallop edges of shells.
Mash potatoes and mix until smooth and fluffy. Add butter, brown sugar, orange juice, rind and salt.
Beat until blended.
Add nuts and sherry.
Place orange shells in heatproof platter and fill with sweet potato mixture.
Dot with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cobbler
directions: Cream together until light and fluffy the butter and first cup of sugar.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter and sugar mixture with 1 cup of milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour fruit over batter and sprinkle with sugar.
Pour over the top 1 or 2 cups of the fruit juice.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal very thin with a meat mallet.
Dip slices in flour; shake off excess.
Brown on both sides in butter in skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Place veal on serving plate; spoon pan juices over veal.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil for exactly 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well. Pour in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain the potatoes and mash with an electric mixer.
Add the cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, butter and pepper.
Mix together on low speed, then whip on high speed until they are light and fluffy.
Spoon into a buttered large casserole or pan.
Dot the potatoes with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
(At this point, you may cool, cover and refrigerate the casserole overnight.)
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with the grated cheese and bake, uncovered, for 30 additional minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Form into desired shape around 8 ounce block of Cheddar cheese. Put into roaster and add 2 cups of water.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove lid for last 10 minutes of baking.
Cool 15 minutes before slicing.

title: golden salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in orange juice, ginger ale and reserved mandarin orange juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Then add mandarin orange sections.
Chill until thickened.

title: texas venison chili
directions: Brown venison in 1/4 cup oil.
Add chopped onion, garlic and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chili powder, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and salt.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
If a thicker chili is desired, stir in 1 tablespoon flour, mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Just before serving, add the cooked kidney beans.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Crush graham crackers and add to melted oleo (mix together). Then put in a 10 x 14-inch pan and press in pan.
Cream powdered sugar and cheese together until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; beat until fluffy.
Spread cherries on.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: orange sherbet and orange salad
directions: Mix the 2 boxes jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package; set aside.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls in hot jello.
Add Dream Whip, drained fruit cocktail and nuts; blend together.
Pour into a long dish or molds.
Use as salad or dessert.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and cook on low fire until vegetables are tender.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: In blender, blend onions and mushrooms with juice.
Pour mixture and remaining ingredients in large pan.
Cook slowly for 4 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs well.
Add the oil.
Add sugar.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
After mixing well, add the vanilla.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Put cake in a cool oven; cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool before taking out of a tube pan.
Don't store airtight.
Top is crunchy and crisp and middle is moist.

title: double lemon cream dessert
directions: Mix with enough beaten egg just to hold together.
Pat into a 10-inch cheesecake pan on the bottom and a little up the sides. Bake 20 minutes at 350° until golden.

title: microwave cheese sauce
directions: Mix butter and flour together in dish and microwave for 45 seconds; stir until smooth.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stop halfway through and stir.
Good over broccoli.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator and let set 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: split pea soup
directions: Open bag of peas and sort them to remove any bad ones.
Follow same procedures with lentils.
Peel and chop onion.
Peel garlic and stick it on a toothpick.
Peel and slice carrots.
Put all the ingredients in a big pan and start measuring water, one cup at a time, into the pan.
Cover the ingredients and add about 2 inches more water.
Add ham ends or chicken bouillon; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover pan, reduce heat to medium-low and allow the soup to cook 1/2 hour or more.
Remove the garlic and take it off the toothpick; smash it with the flat side of a knife.
Scrape the garlic back onto the knife and stir it back into the soup. Continue cooking 2 to 3 hours, adding water if soup seems too thick.
Stir once in a while.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with corn bread or crackers.
This soup freezes well.
(Try not to eat it the night before you plan to be around people you want to impress.)

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Press out crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Beat the eggs with the milk.
Place the sausage on top of the crescent rolls.
Slowly pour egg mixture over the sausage. Top with frozen shredded hash browns, cheese, green pepper, onion and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crock pot recipe - hungarian goulash
directions: Cook steak cubes in flour.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Cook on high for 5 hours.
Add sour cream 30 minutes before serving.
Serve over noodles.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, alternately with flour.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool about 10 minutes on wire rack. Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: fran's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; beat in eggs, molasses and vanilla. Mix remaining ingredients together except raisins and nuts.
Stir to blend.
Add raisins and nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
These cookies stay soft.

title: blueberry lattice coffeecake
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tsp. sugar in warm water in large bowl. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: peppi potato salad
directions: In gallon size bag, add onion, parsley, dressing and pepperoni. Add warm potatoes to bag.
Seal and shake until all ingredients are coated well.
Set aside to marinate at room temperature, shaking now and then.

title: kolachy
directions: Add flour to margarine and crumble.
Add ice cream.
Work in dough.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; cut squares or circles.
Place Solo filling in center of square; pinch corners together.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: candy jewels
directions: Mix Sure-Jell, water and soda in
4-quart saucepan.
(Mixture will foam slightly.)
Mix sugar, corn syrup and Kool-Aid in another saucepan.
Place both pans over high heat and cook both, stirring alternately, until foam has thinned from pectin mixture and sugar mixture is boiling rapidly, 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour pectin mixture in slow, steady stream into boiling sugar mixture, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute longer.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Let stand at room temperature until cool and firm, about 3 hours.
Invert onto sugar-coated wax paper. Cut into 3/4-inch squares with spatula dipped in warm water. Roll in additional sugar to prevent stickiness.
Let stand overnight, uncovered, at room temperature before packaging or storing.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In same liquid, bring beans to boil and simmer until tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Drain, reserving liquid. Preheat oven to 275° to 300°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Stir in flour.
Roll dough into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press balls down with a fork.
Bake at 350° until done.
These cookies stay soft.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook onion in melted margarine until limp and transparent. Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: ice cream coffee
directions: Make
coffee
with
cinnamon
stick.
Remove
cinnamon stick. Pour
coffee into punch bowl and cool.
Add ice cream. Just before
serving, fold in whipped cream.
Three teaspoons sugar may be added to whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: savory herbed oatcakes
directions: Place all ingredients except water in food processor, using pulse setting.
Slowly add water until dough forms a sticky ball. Roll out on a floured board to about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into squares or rounds and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick well and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Cool on rack.
Can be frozen.

title: honey-baked chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken and dip in butter.
Roll in a mixture of the dry ingredients and place in a foil-lined pan.
Combine leftover butter and remaining liquid ingredients and pour over chicken in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, covered in foil.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry or lemon punch
directions: Mix well and pour into a gallon pitcher and finish filling with water.
A bottle of 7-Up or Sprite may be added instead of water.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 1/4 cups sugar, lemon juice and rind. Add egg yolks and mix together. Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat, then boil gently for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked crust.
Beat egg whites until a little stiff.
Add a pinch of cream of tartar. Continue beating until stiff. Add 4 to 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on pie. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil and stir 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Stir until all mixed well and pour immediately into 8-inch square buttered pan.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Combine the evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and margarine and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add the coconut and pecans.
Cool until spreading consistency, beating occasionally.

title: quick fried spinach and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
In a large frying pan or wok, cook onion in vegetable oil for a few minutes until translucent.
Add garlic and stir, cooking for 1 minute.
Add spinach and toss until spinach wilts.
Add rice, salt, pepper and nutmeg to spinach mixture; toss together until mixed well and heated through.
Remove from pan and serve. Serves 4.

title: quick fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in double boiler, except nuts and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until ingredients are melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast corn flakes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and sugar.
Pour over cereal. Stir until evenly
coated.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for top.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Put 1/2 stick of margarine in a pan and melt.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients except peaches.
Pour batter in over melted margarine.
Place peaches over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings and drums
directions: Season chicken with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dip pieces into egg.
Roll in cornstarch. Fry in oil until browned. Arrange meat in foil lined pan. Combine shoyu, ketchup, sugar, vinegar and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn meat every 15 minutes. Serves 6.
Mmmmmm....it's sooo good!

title: sauerkraut chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine with a fork.
Cream butter with electric mixer.
On medium speed, gradually add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add liquid and dry ingredients alternately, beginning and ending with flour; stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (or until cakes test done).
Fill and frost with Mocha Whipped Cream Frosting (recipe follows).

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate; add sugar and mix.
Add well-beaten egg, vanilla and salt.
Premelted chocolate may be used.
Makes enough frosting for a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Frost brownies as soon as they come out of oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place salad in bowl in layers.
Top with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
If strawberries are still frozen, go ahead and put in Jell-O and break up with spoon.
Mix in cranberry sauce.
Chill in bowl or holiday mold.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.

title: peach viennese torte
directions: Cream margarine and confectioners sugar together, adding sugar gradually.
Add flour and mix to form a soft dough.
Pat on bottom and sides of
12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Stir in gelatin.
Allow to cool.
While cooling, arrange peeled, sliced peaches in a single layer over baked shell.
Spread gelatin glaze over peaches. Chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: maria's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: merry's favorite hot wings
directions: Split wings and throw away tips.
Put wings in baking pan; sprinkle with seasoning salt and bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.
While chicken is baking, mix butter, cayenne pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat sauce mixture in microwave for 1 minute and stir.
When chicken is done, dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Bleu cheese dressing.

title: chicken delight
directions: Dice chicken breasts into bite size pieces; set aside.
Dice onion and slice mushrooms; saute in butter in a medium frying pan. Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add chicken pieces and simmer until chicken is cooked.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions. Put chicken sauce over rice.

title: moist banana cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening, buttermilk and bananas.
Beat vigorously with spoon for 2 minutes or medium speed for 2 minutes with electric mixer. Add buttermilk and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for layers, or 45 minutes for oblong pan.

title: granny's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs real good.
Then mix all ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until you can stick knife in the middle and it comes out clean.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Spread in buttered pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: range cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt, quick cooking oats, dry cereal.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in double boiler. Add chopped artichoke hearts to warm. Serve warm with chips.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan over medium-hi heat.
Then add the next 3 ingredients and saute until translucent.
In a large skillet cook ground sirloin (or ground beef) until browned (no raw meat left).
Remove from heat and drain off any fat.
Combine sauteed vegetables with ground sirloin.
Add the last 3 ingredients and season to taste.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until thickened. Serve over toast or butter toasted buns.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate.

title: barbecue beans and franks
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir together first three ingredients.
Cook 4 minutes on High setting.
Stir; cook 4 more minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter or margarine and cook 30 seconds.
Stir in soda.
Pour into buttered pan and let stand 15 minutes or until hard.
Break apart.

title: texas chile hominy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour in baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
